1
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,798
Echo Three to Echo Seven.

2
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:36,800
Han, old buddy, do you read me?

3
00:03:36,884 --> 00:03:38,802
<i>Loud and clear, kid. What’s up?</i>

4
00:03:38,886 --> 00:03:39,845
I finished my circle.

5
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:41,680
I don’t pick up any life readings.

6
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:45,017
<i>There isn’t enough life on this ice cube</i>
<i>to fill a space cruiser.</i>

7
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,935
<i>Sensors are placed. I’m going back.</i>

8
00:03:47,019 --> 00:03:48,812
Right. I’ll see you shortly.

9
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,772
There’s a meteorite
that hit the ground near here.

10
00:03:50,856 --> 00:03:53,192
I want to check it out. It won’t take long.

11
00:03:53,275 --> 00:03:54,693
[Braying]

12
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:57,196
Steady, girl. What’s the matter?

13
00:03:57,279 --> 00:03:59,239
You smell something?

14
00:03:59,323 --> 00:04:00,782
Rrraaah!

15
00:04:39,863 --> 00:04:41,240
Chewie!

16
00:04:41,323 --> 00:04:43,784
Chewie?

17
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,118
Chewie!

18
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:49,831
All right! Don’t lose your temper.

19
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:52,084
I’ll come right back and give you a hand.

20
00:05:12,813 --> 00:05:13,897
Solo?

21
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:16,149
No sign of life out there, General.

22
00:05:16,233 --> 00:05:17,526
The sensors are in place.

23
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:18,902
You’ll know if anything comes around.

24
00:05:18,986 --> 00:05:20,445
Commander Skywalker reported in yet?

25
00:05:20,529 --> 00:05:22,865
No. He’s checking out
a meteorite that hit near him.

26
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:24,992
With all the meteor activity
in this system,

27
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:26,827
it’s going to be difficult to spot
approaching ships.

28
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:29,121
General, I got to leave. I can’t stay anymore.

29
00:05:29,204 --> 00:05:30,163
I’m sorry to hear that.

30
00:05:30,247 --> 00:05:31,373
Well, there’s a price on my head.

31
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:32,958
If I don’t pay off Jabba the Hutt,

32
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,251
I’m a dead man.

33
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,420
A death mark’s not
an easy thing to live with.

34
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:38,005
You’re a good fighter, Solo.

35
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:40,090
I hate to lose you.

36
00:05:40,174 --> 00:05:42,092
Thank you, General.

37
00:05:49,016 --> 00:05:52,186
Well, Your Highness, guess this is it.

38
00:05:52,269 --> 00:05:54,188
That’s right.

39
00:05:54,271 --> 00:05:57,816
Well, don’t get all mushy on me.

40
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,401
So long, Princess.

41
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:04,281
Han!

42
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:06,283
Yes, Your Highnessness?

43
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:08,368
I thought you had decided to stay.

44
00:06:08,452 --> 00:06:11,455
Well, the bounty hunter we ran into
in Ord Mantell changed my mind.

45
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,498
Han, we need you!

46
00:06:13,582 --> 00:06:14,583
<i>We need?</i>

47
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:15,834
Yes.

48
00:06:15,918 --> 00:06:16,919
<i>Well, what about you need?</i>

49
00:06:17,002 --> 00:06:18,003
<i>I need?</i>

50
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:20,297
I don’t know what you’re talking about.

51
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,174
You probably don’t.

52
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:24,092
And what precisely am I supposed to know?

53
00:06:24,176 --> 00:06:26,011
Come on!

54
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:28,305
You want me to stay
because of the way you feel about me.

55
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:31,099
Yes! You’re a great help to us.
You’re a natural leader.

56
00:06:31,183 --> 00:06:33,852
No! That’s not it.

57
00:06:33,936 --> 00:06:35,270
Come on.

58
00:06:35,354 --> 00:06:36,855
A-ha!

59
00:06:36,939 --> 00:06:38,315
You’re imagining things.

60
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,192
Am I? Then why are you following me?

61
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:43,195
Afraid I was gonna leave
without giving you a good-bye kiss?

62
00:06:43,278 --> 00:06:44,613
I’d just as soon kiss a Wookiee!

63
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:46,198
I can arrange that.

64
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:48,283
You could use a good kiss!

65
00:06:49,451 --> 00:06:52,621
I didn’t ask you to turn on the thermal heater.

66
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:56,208
I merely commented that it was freezing
in the princess’s chamber.

67
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:58,627
How will we dry out her clothes?

68
00:06:58,877 --> 00:06:59,878
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

69
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:01,380
Oh, switch off!

70
00:07:01,463 --> 00:07:04,633
Why did you take this apart now?
I’m trying to get us out of here, and you pull both-

71
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:05,884
Excuse me, sir.

72
00:07:05,968 --> 00:07:06,885
Put them back together now!

73
00:07:06,969 --> 00:07:08,262
Might I have a word with you, please?

74
00:07:08,345 --> 00:07:09,304
What do you want?

75
00:07:09,388 --> 00:07:11,890
Well, it’s Princess Leia, sir.
She’s been trying to get you on the communicator.

76
00:07:11,974 --> 00:07:14,226
I turned it off.
I don’t want to talk to her.

77
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:16,228
Well, Princess Leia
is wondering about Master Luke.

78
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:18,188
He hasn’t come back yet.
She doesn’t know where he is.

79
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:19,273
I don’t know where he is.

80
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:20,357
Nobody knows where he is.

81
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,650
What do you mean, nobody knows?

82
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,652
Well, uh, you see-
Deck Officer!

83
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:25,237
Deck Officer!
Excuse me, sir, might I-

84
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,280
Yes, sir?

85
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:27,656
Do you know where Commander Skywalker is?

86
00:07:27,906 --> 00:07:29,241
I haven’t seen him.

87
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:30,659
It’s possible he came through
the south entrance.

88
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:33,412
<i>It’s possible?</i>
<i>Why don’t you go find out?</i>

89
00:07:33,495 --> 00:07:34,580
It’s getting dark out there.

90
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,039
Yes, sir.

91
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:38,250
Excuse me, sir.
Might I inquire what’s going on?

92
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,459
Why not?

93
00:07:39,543 --> 00:07:40,669
Impossible man.

94
00:07:40,919 --> 00:07:42,254
Come along, R2, let’s find Princess Leia.

95
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:43,422
Between ourselves,

96
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:46,216
I think Master Luke is in considerable danger.

97
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,927
[Braying]

98
00:07:55,684 --> 00:07:58,061
Sir, Commander Skywalker
hasn’t come in the south entrance.

99
00:07:58,145 --> 00:07:59,354
He might have forgotten to check in.

100
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:00,522
Not likely. Are the speeders ready?

101
00:08:00,606 --> 00:08:02,941
Uh, not yet. We’re having trouble
adapting them to the cold.

102
00:08:03,025 --> 00:08:04,109
We’ll have to go out on tauntauns.

103
00:08:04,193 --> 00:08:05,944
Sir, the temperature’s dropping too rapidly.

104
00:08:06,028 --> 00:08:08,280
That’s right,
and my friend’s out in it.

105
00:08:12,451 --> 00:08:15,162
Your tauntaun will freeze
before you reach the first marker.

106
00:08:15,245 --> 00:08:17,706
Then I’ll see you in hell. Hyah!

107
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:43,315
Rrraaah!

108
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:50,531
[Grumbling]

109
00:09:35,701 --> 00:09:37,244
Grrrr!

110
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:53,802
Graaah!

111
00:10:32,549 --> 00:10:35,260
<i>[Blip Beep Beep]</i>

112
00:10:35,344 --> 00:10:37,095
You must come along now, R2.

113
00:10:37,179 --> 00:10:39,223
There’s really nothing more we can do.

114
00:10:39,306 --> 00:10:41,517
And my joints are freezing up.

115
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,601
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

116
00:10:42,684 --> 00:10:44,102
Don’t say things like that!

117
00:10:44,186 --> 00:10:45,562
Of course we’ll see Master Luke again.

118
00:10:45,646 --> 00:10:49,149
And he’ll be quite all right. You’ll see.

119
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:51,109
Stupid little short circuit.

120
00:10:51,193 --> 00:10:53,278
He’ll be quite all right.

121
00:10:53,362 --> 00:10:54,571
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

122
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:52,671
Sir, all the patrols are in.

123
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:53,755
Still no-

124
00:11:54,798 --> 00:11:57,676
Still no contact from Skywalker or Solo.

125
00:11:57,759 --> 00:12:01,513
Mistress Leia, R2 says he’s been
quite unable to pick up any signals,

126
00:12:01,597 --> 00:12:05,767
although he does admit that his own range
is far too weak to abandon all hope.

127
00:12:05,851 --> 00:12:07,686
Your Highness,
there’s nothing more we can do tonight.

128
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:10,189
The shield doors must be closed.

129
00:12:11,481 --> 00:12:12,441
Close the doors.

130
00:12:12,524 --> 00:12:13,525
Yes, sir.

131
00:12:13,609 --> 00:12:15,360
<i>[Beep Beep Beep]</i>

132
00:12:15,444 --> 00:12:20,449
R2 says the chances of survival are 725 to 1.

133
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:30,417
Gahhh!

134
00:12:30,501 --> 00:12:35,297
Actually, R2 has been known to make mistakes...

135
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,219
from time to time.

136
00:12:40,302 --> 00:12:41,678
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

137
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:44,598
<i>[Beep Beep Beep]</i>

138
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:46,600
Don’t worry about Master Luke.

139
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:48,227
I’m sure he’ll be all right.

140
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:50,687
He’s quite clever, you know, for a human being.

141
00:13:06,370 --> 00:13:07,704
<i>Luke.</i>

142
00:13:10,374 --> 00:13:11,667
<i>Luke.</i>

143
00:13:19,258 --> 00:13:20,676
Ben?

144
00:13:20,759 --> 00:13:23,470
<i>You will go to the Dagobah system.</i>

145
00:13:23,554 --> 00:13:25,389
Dagobah system?

146
00:13:25,472 --> 00:13:28,267
<i>There you will learn from Yoda,</i>

147
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:32,771
<i>the Jedi master who instructed me.</i>

148
00:13:32,855 --> 00:13:34,731
Ben!

149
00:13:34,815 --> 00:13:36,024
Ben!

150
00:13:36,275 --> 00:13:38,527
[Braying]

151
00:13:40,404 --> 00:13:41,738
Han: Luke!

152
00:13:41,822 --> 00:13:44,366
Luke!

153
00:13:50,789 --> 00:13:52,708
Don’t do this, Luke.

154
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:56,378
Come on, give me a sign here.

155
00:14:17,608 --> 00:14:19,401
Not much time.

156
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:20,652
Ben.

157
00:14:20,736 --> 00:14:22,946
Ben.

158
00:14:26,742 --> 00:14:28,410
Hang on, kid.

159
00:14:29,578 --> 00:14:31,622
Dagobah system.

160
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:32,664
Whew!

161
00:14:32,748 --> 00:14:35,667
This may smell bad, kid...

162
00:14:35,751 --> 00:14:37,753
Yoda.

163
00:14:37,836 --> 00:14:39,588
but it’ll keep you warm...

164
00:14:39,671 --> 00:14:41,840
till I get the shelter up.

165
00:14:41,924 --> 00:14:44,551
Ben...Dagobah...

166
00:14:44,635 --> 00:14:46,345
Ahhh!

167
00:14:46,428 --> 00:14:52,518
Ah! I thought they smelled bad on the outside!

168
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:36,979
Echo Base, I’ve got something.

169
00:15:37,062 --> 00:15:40,148
Not much, but it could be a life-form.

170
00:15:44,111 --> 00:15:46,613
Commander Skywalker, do you copy?

171
00:15:46,697 --> 00:15:48,615
This is Rogue Two.

172
00:15:48,699 --> 00:15:51,076
This is Rogue Two.

173
00:15:51,159 --> 00:15:54,872
Captain Solo, do you copy?

174
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:03,589
Commander Skywalker, do you copy?

175
00:16:03,672 --> 00:16:06,008
This is Rogue Two.

176
00:16:06,091 --> 00:16:07,593
<i>Han: Good morning.</i>

177
00:16:07,676 --> 00:16:09,970
<i>Nice of you guys to drop by.</i>

178
00:16:10,053 --> 00:16:12,556
Echo Base, this is Rogue Two.

179
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:13,932
I’ve found them.

180
00:16:14,016 --> 00:16:15,893
Repeat, I’ve found them.

181
00:16:46,089 --> 00:16:48,800
Master Luke, sir, it’s so good
to see you fully functional again.

182
00:16:48,884 --> 00:16:49,843
Thanks, 3PO.

183
00:16:49,927 --> 00:16:50,928
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

184
00:16:51,011 --> 00:16:52,721
R2 expresses his relief also.

185
00:16:52,804 --> 00:16:55,599
How ya feelin’, kid?
You don’t look so bad to me.

186
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:58,977
You look strong enough
to pull the ears off a gundark.

187
00:16:59,061 --> 00:17:00,604
Thanks to you.

188
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:03,148
That’s two you owe me, junior.

189
00:17:03,232 --> 00:17:04,900
Well, Your Worship,

190
00:17:04,983 --> 00:17:07,861
looks like you managed to keep me around
for a little while longer.

191
00:17:07,945 --> 00:17:09,613
I had nothing to do with it.

192
00:17:09,696 --> 00:17:12,699
General Rieekan thinks it’s dangerous
for any ships to leave the system

193
00:17:12,783 --> 00:17:14,034
until we’ve activated the energy field.

194
00:17:14,117 --> 00:17:16,036
That’s a good story.

195
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:20,082
<i>I think you just can’t bear to let</i>
<i>a gorgeous guy like me out of your sight.</i>

196
00:17:20,165 --> 00:17:23,627
I don’t know where
you get your delusions, laser brain.

197
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:25,254
Hah hah hah!

198
00:17:26,713 --> 00:17:28,632
Laugh it up, fuzzball,

199
00:17:28,715 --> 00:17:32,010
but you didn’t see us alone
in the south passage.

200
00:17:32,094 --> 00:17:34,680
She expressed her true feelings for me.

201
00:17:34,763 --> 00:17:36,014
My-

202
00:17:36,098 --> 00:17:39,059
Why, you stuck-up, half-witted,

203
00:17:39,142 --> 00:17:41,812
scruffy-looking nerf herder!

204
00:17:41,895 --> 00:17:44,982
Who’s scruffy-looking?

205
00:17:47,526 --> 00:17:51,780
I must have hit pretty close to the mark
to get her all riled up like that, huh, kid?

206
00:17:55,117 --> 00:17:58,745
Well, I guess you don’t know
everything about women yet.

207
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:07,045
<i>Headquarters personnel,</i>
<i>report to command center.</i>

208
00:18:09,882 --> 00:18:13,051
<i>Headquarters personnel,</i>
<i>report to command center.</i>

209
00:18:13,135 --> 00:18:14,136
Take it easy.

210
00:18:14,219 --> 00:18:16,763
Excuse us, please.

211
00:18:19,641 --> 00:18:21,727
Princess, we have a visitor.

212
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:25,564
Picked up something
outside the base’s Zone 12 moving east.

213
00:18:25,647 --> 00:18:26,607
It’s metal.

214
00:18:26,690 --> 00:18:27,941
Then it couldn’t be one of those creatures.

215
00:18:28,025 --> 00:18:29,610
Could be a speeder, one of ours.

216
00:18:29,693 --> 00:18:30,903
No.

217
00:18:30,986 --> 00:18:32,029
Wait.

218
00:18:32,112 --> 00:18:34,823
There’s something
very weak coming through.

219
00:18:34,907 --> 00:18:37,993
[Radio Static]

220
00:18:38,076 --> 00:18:41,163
Sir, I’m fluent in six million
forms of communication.

221
00:18:41,246 --> 00:18:43,916
This signal is not used by the Alliance.

222
00:18:43,999 --> 00:18:46,168
It could be an imperial code.

223
00:18:49,755 --> 00:18:51,590
It isn’t friendly, whatever it is.

224
00:18:51,673 --> 00:18:53,592
Come on, Chewie, let’s check it out.

225
00:18:53,675 --> 00:18:56,887
Send Rogues 10 and 11 to Station 38.

226
00:19:13,028 --> 00:19:14,238
Grrr!

227
00:19:28,085 --> 00:19:29,962
Gahhh!

228
00:19:31,839 --> 00:19:32,965
<i>I’m afraid there’s not much left.</i>

229
00:19:33,048 --> 00:19:34,007
What was it?

230
00:19:34,091 --> 00:19:35,634
<i>Droid of some kind.</i>

231
00:19:35,717 --> 00:19:37,636
<i>I didn’t hit it that hard.</i>
<i>Must’ve had a self-destruct.</i>

232
00:19:37,719 --> 00:19:39,304
An imperial probe droid.

233
00:19:39,388 --> 00:19:42,641
<i>It’s a good bet the Empire knows we’re here.</i>

234
00:19:42,724 --> 00:19:44,726
We’d better start the evacuation.

235
00:20:29,021 --> 00:20:30,814
Admiral.

236
00:20:30,898 --> 00:20:32,191
Yes, Captain?

237
00:20:32,274 --> 00:20:34,693
I think we’ve got something, sir.

238
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:38,363
The report is only a fragment
from a probe droid in the Hoth system,

239
00:20:38,447 --> 00:20:39,823
but it’s the best lead we’ve had.

240
00:20:39,907 --> 00:20:42,910
We have thousands of probe droids
searching the galaxy.

241
00:20:42,993 --> 00:20:44,077
I want proof, not leads.

242
00:20:44,161 --> 00:20:46,038
The visuals indicate life readings.

243
00:20:46,121 --> 00:20:47,080
It could mean anything.

244
00:20:47,164 --> 00:20:48,373
If we followed up every lead-

245
00:20:48,457 --> 00:20:51,710
But, sir, the Hoth system
is supposed to be devoid of humans.

246
00:20:51,793 --> 00:20:52,920
You’ve found something?

247
00:20:53,003 --> 00:20:54,129
Yes, my lord.

248
00:20:56,465 --> 00:20:58,884
That’s it. The rebels are there.

249
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:03,388
My lord, there are so many
uncharted settlements.

250
00:21:03,472 --> 00:21:04,473
It could be smugglers-

251
00:21:04,723 --> 00:21:06,266
That is the system.

252
00:21:06,350 --> 00:21:08,894
And I’m sure Skywalker is with them.

253
00:21:08,977 --> 00:21:11,980
Set your course for the Hoth system.

254
00:21:12,064 --> 00:21:14,233
General Veers, prepare your men.

255
00:21:14,316 --> 00:21:15,817
Admiral.

256
00:21:22,157 --> 00:21:24,868
Groups 7 and 10 will stay behind
to fly the speeders.

257
00:21:24,952 --> 00:21:26,411
As soon as each transport is loaded,

258
00:21:26,495 --> 00:21:28,747
evacuation control will give clearance
for immediate launch.

259
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:29,831
Right, sir.

260
00:21:32,918 --> 00:21:35,003
All right! That’s it.

261
00:21:35,087 --> 00:21:36,129
Try it.

262
00:21:37,965 --> 00:21:41,051
Oh! Turn it off! Turn it off!

263
00:21:41,134 --> 00:21:43,262
Turn it off!

264
00:21:43,345 --> 00:21:47,057
Sir, it will take quite a while
to evacuate the T-47s.

265
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:48,100
Forget the heavy equipment.

266
00:21:48,183 --> 00:21:51,061
There’s plenty of time to get
the smaller modules on the transports.

267
00:21:51,144 --> 00:21:52,104
Take care, sir.

268
00:21:52,187 --> 00:21:53,188
Thanks.

269
00:21:56,191 --> 00:21:59,319
Chewie, take care of yourself, O.K.?

270
00:22:02,948 --> 00:22:04,867
O.K., O.K.!

271
00:22:06,326 --> 00:22:07,870
Hi, kid.

272
00:22:07,953 --> 00:22:10,372
There’s got to be a reason for it.
Check it at the other end.

273
00:22:10,455 --> 00:22:11,832
Wait a second.

274
00:22:12,916 --> 00:22:14,209
You all right?

275
00:22:14,293 --> 00:22:15,544
Yeah.

276
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:24,303
Be careful.

277
00:22:24,386 --> 00:22:26,221
You, too.

278
00:22:31,226 --> 00:22:37,107
General, there’s a fleet of Stardestroyers
coming out of hyperspace in Sector Four.

279
00:22:37,191 --> 00:22:40,110
Reroute all power to the energy shield.

280
00:22:40,194 --> 00:22:43,113
We gotta hold them till all transports are away.

281
00:22:43,197 --> 00:22:44,573
Prepare for ground assault.

282
00:22:58,587 --> 00:23:00,422
What is it, General?

283
00:23:00,506 --> 00:23:02,257
My lord, the fleet
has moved out of light speed.

284
00:23:02,341 --> 00:23:07,095
ComScan has detected an energy field protecting
an area of the sixth planet of the Hoth system.

285
00:23:07,179 --> 00:23:09,848
The field is strong enough
to deflect any bombardment.

286
00:23:09,932 --> 00:23:12,518
The rebels are alerted to our presence.

287
00:23:12,601 --> 00:23:15,521
Admiral Ozzel came out of light speed
too close to the system.

288
00:23:15,604 --> 00:23:17,523
He-He felt surprise was wiser.

289
00:23:17,606 --> 00:23:20,192
He is as clumsy as he is stupid.

290
00:23:20,275 --> 00:23:23,529
General, prepare your troops
for a surface attack.

291
00:23:23,612 --> 00:23:25,197
Yes, my lord.

292
00:23:32,204 --> 00:23:33,872
Lord Vader.

293
00:23:33,956 --> 00:23:36,124
The fleet has moved out of light speed,
and we’re preparing to-

294
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:37,876
Aaugh!

295
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:41,547
You have failed me for the last time, Admiral.

296
00:23:41,630 --> 00:23:42,965
Captain Piett.

297
00:23:43,048 --> 00:23:44,550
Yes, my lord?

298
00:23:44,633 --> 00:23:47,636
Make ready to land our troops
beyond their energy field

299
00:23:47,886 --> 00:23:50,889
and deploy the fleet
so that nothing gets off the system.

300
00:23:50,973 --> 00:23:54,142
You are in command now, Admiral Piett.

301
00:23:54,226 --> 00:23:55,561
Thank you, Lord Vader.

302
00:23:55,644 --> 00:23:57,062
[Gagging]

303
00:23:57,229 --> 00:24:00,482
All troop carriers will assemble
at the north entrance.

304
00:24:00,566 --> 00:24:03,402
The heavy transport ships
will leave as soon as they’re loaded.

305
00:24:03,485 --> 00:24:05,571
Only two fighter escorts per ship.

306
00:24:05,654 --> 00:24:08,448
The energy shield
can only be opened for a short time,

307
00:24:08,532 --> 00:24:11,076
so you’ll have to stay very close
to your transports.

308
00:24:11,159 --> 00:24:13,495
Two fighters against a Stardestroyer?

309
00:24:13,579 --> 00:24:16,081
The ion cannon
will fire several shots

310
00:24:16,164 --> 00:24:19,168
to make sure that any enemy ships
will be out of your flight path.

311
00:24:19,251 --> 00:24:21,336
When you’ve gotten past the energy shield,

312
00:24:21,420 --> 00:24:23,505
proceed directly to the rendezvous point.

313
00:24:23,589 --> 00:24:25,090
Understood?

314
00:24:25,174 --> 00:24:26,508
Good luck.

315
00:24:26,592 --> 00:24:28,510
O.K. Everybody to your stations.

316
00:24:28,594 --> 00:24:30,012
Let’s go.

317
00:24:47,029 --> 00:24:50,324
Their primary target will be
the power generators.

318
00:24:50,407 --> 00:24:52,159
Prepare to open shield.

319
00:24:57,956 --> 00:25:00,125
Sir, rebel ships are coming into our sector.

320
00:25:00,209 --> 00:25:02,294
Good. Our first catch of the day.

321
00:25:04,046 --> 00:25:06,048
Stand by, ion control.

322
00:25:07,424 --> 00:25:08,425
Fire.

323
00:25:22,439 --> 00:25:26,652
<i>The first transport is away.</i>

324
00:25:26,735 --> 00:25:30,322
<i>The first transport is away.</i>

325
00:25:36,161 --> 00:25:38,038
Feeling all right, sir?

326
00:25:38,121 --> 00:25:39,748
Just like new, Dak. How about you?

327
00:25:39,998 --> 00:25:43,043
Right now I feel I could take on
the whole Empire myself.

328
00:25:43,126 --> 00:25:45,295
I know what you mean.

329
00:26:03,522 --> 00:26:04,648
Echo Station Three-T-Eight.

330
00:26:04,731 --> 00:26:06,525
We’ve spotted imperial walkers.

331
00:26:06,608 --> 00:26:09,027
<i>Imperial walkers on the north ridge.</i>

332
00:26:09,111 --> 00:26:12,489
[Thudding]

333
00:26:31,508 --> 00:26:33,802
Echo Station Five-Seven. We’re on our way.

334
00:26:39,308 --> 00:26:41,310
All right, boys, keep tight now.

335
00:26:41,393 --> 00:26:43,520
Luke, I have no approach vector.
I’m not set.

336
00:26:43,604 --> 00:26:45,189
Steady, Dak.

337
00:26:45,272 --> 00:26:47,149
Attack pattern Delta. Go now.

338
00:26:50,777 --> 00:26:52,529
All right. I’m coming in.

339
00:26:57,117 --> 00:26:59,244
Hobbie, you still with me?

340
00:27:20,724 --> 00:27:22,851
That armor’s too strong for blasters.

341
00:27:25,395 --> 00:27:27,564
Rogue Group,
use your harpoons and tow cables.

342
00:27:27,648 --> 00:27:31,443
Go for the legs.
It might be our only chance of stopping them.

343
00:27:31,527 --> 00:27:33,487
All right. Stand by, Dak.

344
00:27:33,570 --> 00:27:36,448
Oh, Luke,
we’ve got a malfunction in fire control.

345
00:27:36,532 --> 00:27:38,492
I’ll have to cut in the auxiliary.

346
00:27:38,575 --> 00:27:41,286
Just hang on. Hang on, Dak.

347
00:27:41,370 --> 00:27:43,497
Get ready to fire that tow cable.

348
00:27:45,707 --> 00:27:46,583
Ah!

349
00:27:48,794 --> 00:27:49,795
Dak?

350
00:27:49,878 --> 00:27:50,879
Dak!

351
00:28:13,902 --> 00:28:16,822
Yes, Lord Vader,
I’ve reached the main power generators.

352
00:28:16,905 --> 00:28:18,490
The shield will be down in moments.

353
00:28:18,574 --> 00:28:21,368
You may start your landing.

354
00:28:24,496 --> 00:28:26,331
Rogue Three.

355
00:28:26,415 --> 00:28:27,541
Copy, Rogue Leader.

356
00:28:27,624 --> 00:28:29,543
Wedge, I’ve lost my gunner.

357
00:28:29,626 --> 00:28:30,836
You’ll have to make this shot.

358
00:28:30,919 --> 00:28:32,713
I’ll cover for you.

359
00:28:32,796 --> 00:28:36,383
Set your harpoon. Follow me on the next pass.

360
00:28:36,466 --> 00:28:38,468
Coming around, Rogue Leader.

361
00:28:41,305 --> 00:28:43,599
Steady, Rogue Two.

362
00:28:43,682 --> 00:28:44,766
Activate harpoon.

363
00:28:47,728 --> 00:28:49,396
Good shot, Janson.

364
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:57,654
One more pass.
Coming around, Wedge.

365
00:29:03,285 --> 00:29:05,495
Cable out. Let her go!

366
00:29:05,579 --> 00:29:07,456
Detach cable.

367
00:29:07,539 --> 00:29:08,665
Cable detached.

368
00:29:16,548 --> 00:29:18,300
Come on.

369
00:29:25,307 --> 00:29:26,683
Hah! That got him!

370
00:29:26,767 --> 00:29:28,644
I see it, Wedge. Good work.

371
00:29:28,810 --> 00:29:31,230
I don’t think we can protect
two transports at a time.

372
00:29:31,313 --> 00:29:33,565
It’s risky, but we can’t hold out much longer.

373
00:29:33,649 --> 00:29:35,901
We have no choice.

374
00:29:35,984 --> 00:29:36,985
Launch patrol.

375
00:29:37,277 --> 00:29:38,904
Evacuate remaining ground staff.

376
00:29:38,987 --> 00:29:40,614
Gahhh!

377
00:29:40,697 --> 00:29:43,242
No, no! No.

378
00:29:43,325 --> 00:29:45,244
This one goes there.

379
00:29:45,327 --> 00:29:47,454
That one goes there, right?

380
00:29:47,538 --> 00:29:51,458
R2, you take good care
of Master Luke now, understand?

381
00:29:51,542 --> 00:29:52,584
<i>[Beeping]</i>

382
00:29:52,668 --> 00:29:54,920
And do take good care of yourself.

383
00:29:55,003 --> 00:29:58,590
<i>[Beep Beep Blip]</i>

384
00:29:58,674 --> 00:30:00,342
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

385
00:30:23,907 --> 00:30:26,285
All troops will debark for ground assault.

386
00:30:26,368 --> 00:30:28,871
Prepare to target the main generator.

387
00:30:32,583 --> 00:30:33,542
Rogue Two, are you all right?

388
00:30:33,625 --> 00:30:35,961
Yeah. I’m with you, Rogue Leader.

389
00:30:36,044 --> 00:30:38,005
Well, set harpoon. I’ll cover for you.

390
00:30:39,590 --> 00:30:40,883
Coming around.

391
00:30:40,966 --> 00:30:43,802
Watch that cross fire, boys.

392
00:30:43,886 --> 00:30:45,762
Set for position three.

393
00:30:45,846 --> 00:30:47,306
Steady.

394
00:30:47,389 --> 00:30:48,599
Stay tight and low.

395
00:30:48,682 --> 00:30:49,808
This is it!

396
00:30:49,892 --> 00:30:51,310
Aah!

397
00:30:55,397 --> 00:30:56,899
Hobbie!

398
00:30:56,982 --> 00:30:58,609
I’ve been hit!

399
00:31:40,692 --> 00:31:42,027
You all right?

400
00:31:42,110 --> 00:31:44,029
Why are you still here?

401
00:31:44,112 --> 00:31:45,697
Heard the command center
had been hit.

402
00:31:45,781 --> 00:31:47,032
You’ve got your clearance to leave.

403
00:31:47,115 --> 00:31:48,992
Don’t worry. I’ll leave.

404
00:31:49,076 --> 00:31:50,827
First I’m gonna get you to your ship.

405
00:31:50,911 --> 00:31:52,579
Your Highness,
we must take this last transport.

406
00:31:52,663 --> 00:31:53,622
It’s our only hope.

407
00:31:53,705 --> 00:31:57,000
Send all troops in Sector 12
to the south slope to protect the fighters.

408
00:31:58,710 --> 00:32:00,671
<i>Imperial troops have entered the base.</i>

409
00:32:00,754 --> 00:32:02,047
<i>Imperial troops</i>
<i>have entered-[Static]</i>

410
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:03,757
Come on. That’s it.

411
00:32:03,841 --> 00:32:06,552
Give the evacuation code signal.

412
00:32:08,846 --> 00:32:10,138
And get to your transports!

413
00:32:10,389 --> 00:32:12,140
Oh! Wait for me!

414
00:32:12,391 --> 00:32:15,727
Begin retreat! Fall back!

415
00:33:14,536 --> 00:33:16,205
Distance to power generators?

416
00:33:16,496 --> 00:33:17,789
<i>17.28.</i>

417
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:28,800
Target. Maximum firepower.

418
00:33:54,535 --> 00:33:57,871
Transport, this is Solo.
Better take off. I can’t get to you.

419
00:33:57,955 --> 00:33:59,831
<i>I’ll get her out on the Falcon.</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

420
00:34:01,083 --> 00:34:03,168
B-B-But where are you going?

421
00:34:03,252 --> 00:34:04,586
Come back!

422
00:34:21,687 --> 00:34:23,188
Wait!

423
00:34:23,272 --> 00:34:25,148
Wait for me! Wait! Stop!

424
00:34:25,232 --> 00:34:26,775
How typical.

425
00:34:26,859 --> 00:34:28,193
Come on.

426
00:34:28,277 --> 00:34:30,112
Gahhh!

427
00:34:31,905 --> 00:34:33,073
Hurry up, goldenrod.

428
00:34:33,156 --> 00:34:35,576
You’re gonna be a permanent resident.

429
00:34:35,659 --> 00:34:36,994
Wait! Wait!

430
00:34:48,589 --> 00:34:52,050
[Engine Stalling]

431
00:34:54,928 --> 00:34:55,929
How’s this?

432
00:34:56,013 --> 00:34:58,056
Would it help if I got out and pushed?

433
00:34:58,140 --> 00:34:59,308
Captain Solo! Captain Solo!

434
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:00,601
It might.

435
00:35:01,768 --> 00:35:04,313
Sir, might I suggest that you-

436
00:35:04,605 --> 00:35:06,148
It can wait.

437
00:35:10,319 --> 00:35:12,738
This bucket of bolts
is never gonna get us past that blockade.

438
00:35:12,821 --> 00:35:15,157
This baby’s got a few surprises
left in her, sweetheart.

439
00:35:23,582 --> 00:35:25,709
Come on! Come on!

440
00:35:25,792 --> 00:35:28,337
Switch over.
Let’s hope we don’t have a burnout.

441
00:35:31,173 --> 00:35:31,924
See?

442
00:35:32,007 --> 00:35:34,301
Someday you’re gonna be wrong,
and I just hope I’m there to see it.

443
00:35:37,137 --> 00:35:38,305
Punch it!

444
00:35:55,948 --> 00:35:57,366
R2!

445
00:35:57,616 --> 00:36:01,119
Get her ready for takeoff.

446
00:36:01,203 --> 00:36:05,666
Good luck, Luke. See you at the rendezvous.

447
00:36:05,749 --> 00:36:07,084
<i>[Blip Beep]</i>

448
00:36:07,167 --> 00:36:09,127
Don’t worry, R2.

449
00:36:09,211 --> 00:36:11,213
We’re going. We’re going.

450
00:36:22,057 --> 00:36:23,642
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

451
00:36:23,725 --> 00:36:25,060
There’s nothing wrong, R2.

452
00:36:25,143 --> 00:36:27,187
I’m just setting a new course.

453
00:36:27,271 --> 00:36:29,857
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

454
00:36:29,940 --> 00:36:32,651
We’re not gonna regroup with the others.

455
00:36:32,734 --> 00:36:34,903
We’re going to the Dagobah system.

456
00:36:34,987 --> 00:36:36,822
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

457
00:36:36,905 --> 00:36:38,824
Yes, R2?

458
00:36:40,325 --> 00:36:42,035
That’s all right.

459
00:36:42,119 --> 00:36:44,746
I’d like to keep it
on manual control for a while.

460
00:36:58,802 --> 00:37:01,180
Gahhh!

461
00:37:01,263 --> 00:37:02,431
I saw ’em! I saw ’em!

462
00:37:02,681 --> 00:37:03,765
Saw what?

463
00:37:03,849 --> 00:37:06,018
Stardestroyers,
two of ’em coming right at us.

464
00:37:06,101 --> 00:37:08,187
Sir! Sir! Might I suggest-

465
00:37:08,270 --> 00:37:10,689
Shut him up or shut him down!

466
00:37:10,772 --> 00:37:12,733
Check the deflector shield.

467
00:37:12,816 --> 00:37:14,735
Great.

468
00:37:14,818 --> 00:37:16,862
Well, we can still outmaneuver them.

469
00:37:21,116 --> 00:37:23,035
Take evasive action!

470
00:37:23,118 --> 00:37:25,204
[Crash]

471
00:37:25,287 --> 00:37:27,039
[Alarm]

472
00:37:34,755 --> 00:37:36,381
Prepare to make the jump
to light speed.

473
00:37:36,465 --> 00:37:37,382
3PO: But, sir!

474
00:37:37,466 --> 00:37:40,177
They’re getting closer.

475
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:42,387
Oh, yeah? Watch this.

476
00:37:42,471 --> 00:37:45,390
[Engine Stalls]

477
00:37:45,474 --> 00:37:46,808
Watch what?

478
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:49,853
I think we’re in trouble.

479
00:37:49,937 --> 00:37:53,482
If I may say so, sir, I noticed earlier
the hyperdrive motivator has been damaged.

480
00:37:53,732 --> 00:37:55,359
It’s impossible to go to light speed.

481
00:37:55,442 --> 00:37:58,111
We’re in trouble.

482
00:38:01,281 --> 00:38:02,491
Horizontal boosters!

483
00:38:02,783 --> 00:38:04,743
Gahhh!

484
00:38:04,826 --> 00:38:06,870
Alluvial dampers.

485
00:38:06,954 --> 00:38:08,497
Ow!

486
00:38:08,747 --> 00:38:10,499
That’s not it.

487
00:38:10,791 --> 00:38:12,251
Bring me the hydrospanner!

488
00:38:14,211 --> 00:38:17,756
I don’t know how
we’re gonna get out of this one.

489
00:38:20,008 --> 00:38:21,176
Ow!

490
00:38:21,260 --> 00:38:22,344
Chewie!

491
00:38:26,515 --> 00:38:28,100
That wasn’t a laser blast. Something hit us.

492
00:38:28,183 --> 00:38:29,810
Han, get up here!

493
00:38:31,311 --> 00:38:32,896
Come on, Chewie!

494
00:38:33,063 --> 00:38:34,773
Asteroids.

495
00:38:34,857 --> 00:38:38,151
Oh, no.

496
00:38:38,235 --> 00:38:39,778
Chewie, set two-seven-one.

497
00:38:39,862 --> 00:38:41,196
What are you doing?

498
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:44,950
You’re not actually going
into an asteroid field?

499
00:38:45,033 --> 00:38:47,953
They’d be crazy to follow us,
wouldn’t they?

500
00:38:50,038 --> 00:38:51,957
You don’t have to do this to impress me.

501
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:56,879
Sir, the possibility of successfully navigating
an asteroid field is approximately 3,720 to 1.

502
00:38:56,962 --> 00:38:58,547
Never tell me the odds!

503
00:39:20,903 --> 00:39:22,529
Look out!

504
00:39:25,157 --> 00:39:28,493
You said you wanted
to be around when I made a mistake.

505
00:39:28,577 --> 00:39:30,329
This could be it, sweetheart.

506
00:39:30,412 --> 00:39:31,413
I take it back.

507
00:39:31,496 --> 00:39:34,499
We’re going to get pulverized
if we stay out here much longer.

508
00:39:34,583 --> 00:39:35,959
Ain’t gonna argue with that.

509
00:39:36,043 --> 00:39:38,504
I’m going in closer to one of the big ones.

510
00:39:38,587 --> 00:39:39,505
Closer?!

511
00:39:39,588 --> 00:39:40,464
3PO: Closer?!

512
00:39:40,547 --> 00:39:41,590
Gahhh!

513
00:40:07,533 --> 00:40:09,451
Oh, this is suicide! There’s nowhere to go.

514
00:40:09,535 --> 00:40:11,537
There. That looks pretty good.

515
00:40:11,620 --> 00:40:13,914
What looks pretty good?

516
00:40:13,997 --> 00:40:15,916
Yeah, that’ll do nicely.

517
00:40:15,999 --> 00:40:19,127
Excuse me, ma’am,
but where are we going?

518
00:40:29,054 --> 00:40:31,515
I hope you know what you’re doing.

519
00:40:31,598 --> 00:40:32,933
Yeah. Me, too.

520
00:40:39,982 --> 00:40:41,316
<i>[Beep Blip Blip!]</i>

521
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,902
Yep, that’s it. Dagobah.

522
00:40:43,986 --> 00:40:46,196
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

523
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:48,448
No, I’m not gonna change my mind about this.

524
00:40:48,532 --> 00:40:51,994
I’m not picking up any cities or technology.

525
00:40:52,077 --> 00:40:54,538
Massive life-form readings, though.

526
00:40:54,621 --> 00:40:57,249
There’s something alive down there.

527
00:40:57,332 --> 00:40:58,667
<i>[Beep?]</i>

528
00:40:58,959 --> 00:41:01,670
Yes. I’m sure it’s perfectly safe for droids.

529
00:41:05,507 --> 00:41:08,260
<i>[Beep Blip Beep!]</i>

530
00:41:08,343 --> 00:41:10,304
I know! I know!

531
00:41:10,387 --> 00:41:13,974
All the scopes are dead. I can’t see a thing.

532
00:41:14,057 --> 00:41:15,267
Just hang on.

533
00:41:15,350 --> 00:41:17,227
I’m gonna start the landing cycle.

534
00:41:38,207 --> 00:41:41,710
<i>[Beep Beep Beep]</i>

535
00:42:08,487 --> 00:42:10,989
<i>[Beep Beep Blip]</i>

536
00:42:11,073 --> 00:42:12,115
No, R2, you stay put.

537
00:42:12,199 --> 00:42:14,076
I’ll have a look around.

538
00:42:17,246 --> 00:42:18,330
[Splash]

539
00:42:18,413 --> 00:42:20,541
R2?

540
00:42:20,624 --> 00:42:21,625
R2!

541
00:42:23,585 --> 00:42:24,711
Where are you?

542
00:42:28,215 --> 00:42:29,633
R2!

543
00:42:36,598 --> 00:42:38,225
You be more careful.

544
00:42:41,186 --> 00:42:44,106
R2, that way.

545
00:43:12,092 --> 00:43:13,385
R2!

546
00:43:28,108 --> 00:43:29,651
<i>Beeep!</i>

547
00:43:41,163 --> 00:43:42,414
Oh, no.

548
00:43:42,497 --> 00:43:44,416
Are you all right?

549
00:43:44,499 --> 00:43:45,834
Come on.

550
00:43:49,213 --> 00:43:51,423
You were lucky to get out of there.

551
00:43:51,507 --> 00:43:53,467
Anything broken?

552
00:43:53,550 --> 00:43:57,137
<i>[Beep Blip Beep]</i>

553
00:43:57,221 --> 00:43:59,765
If you’re saying coming here was a bad idea,

554
00:43:59,848 --> 00:44:01,433
I’m beginning to agree with you.

555
00:44:01,517 --> 00:44:03,101
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

556
00:44:03,185 --> 00:44:05,270
R2, what are we doing here?

557
00:44:05,354 --> 00:44:10,776
It’s like...something out of a dream or...

558
00:44:10,859 --> 00:44:12,486
I don’t know.

559
00:44:12,569 --> 00:44:15,113
Maybe I’m just going crazy.

560
00:44:46,562 --> 00:44:48,272
Yes, Admiral?

561
00:44:48,355 --> 00:44:51,233
<i>Our ships have sighted</i>
<i>the Millennium Falcon, lord,</i>

562
00:44:51,316 --> 00:44:54,403
but it has entered an asteroid field,
and we cannot risk-

563
00:44:54,486 --> 00:44:56,530
Asteroids do not concern me, Admiral.

564
00:44:56,613 --> 00:44:59,825
I want that ship, not excuses.

565
00:44:59,908 --> 00:45:02,160
Yes, lord.

566
00:45:05,914 --> 00:45:09,918
I’m gonna shut down everything
but the emergency power systems.

567
00:45:10,169 --> 00:45:14,173
Sir, I’m almost afraid to ask,
but does that include shutting me down, too?

568
00:45:14,256 --> 00:45:16,508
<i>No. I need you to talk to the Falcon.</i>

569
00:45:16,592 --> 00:45:19,678
Find out what’s wrong with the hyperdrive.

570
00:45:26,435 --> 00:45:29,730
Sir, it’s quite possible
this asteroid is not entirely stable.

571
00:45:29,813 --> 00:45:32,316
Not entirely stable?

572
00:45:32,399 --> 00:45:33,942
I’m glad you’re here to tell us these things.

573
00:45:34,193 --> 00:45:37,529
Chewie, take the professor in the back
and plug him into the hyperdrive.

574
00:45:37,613 --> 00:45:40,532
Sometimes I just don’t understand
human behavior.

575
00:45:40,616 --> 00:45:42,951
After all, I’m only trying to do my job.

576
00:45:47,789 --> 00:45:49,291
Let go.
Shh!

577
00:45:50,959 --> 00:45:52,377
Let go, please.

578
00:45:52,461 --> 00:45:53,712
Don’t get excited.

579
00:45:53,795 --> 00:45:57,591
Captain, being held by you
isn’t quite enough to get me excited.

580
00:45:57,674 --> 00:45:59,218
Sorry, sweetheart.

581
00:45:59,301 --> 00:46:01,970
I haven’t got time for anything else.

582
00:46:36,672 --> 00:46:38,465
Ready for some power?

583
00:46:38,549 --> 00:46:40,342
O.K.

584
00:46:43,554 --> 00:46:44,888
Let’s see now.

585
00:46:44,972 --> 00:46:46,765
Put that in there.

586
00:46:46,849 --> 00:46:48,016
There you go.

587
00:46:49,685 --> 00:46:53,772
Now all I gotta do is find this Yoda...

588
00:46:53,856 --> 00:46:55,440
if he even exists.

589
00:47:01,572 --> 00:47:05,659
It’s really a strange place
to find a Jedi master.

590
00:47:05,742 --> 00:47:08,036
This place gives me the creeps.

591
00:47:11,707 --> 00:47:14,751
Still...

592
00:47:14,835 --> 00:47:16,712
there’s something familiar about this place.

593
00:47:16,795 --> 00:47:18,797
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

594
00:47:18,881 --> 00:47:20,424
I don’t know.

595
00:47:20,507 --> 00:47:21,592
I feel like-

596
00:47:21,675 --> 00:47:23,844
Feel like what?

597
00:47:23,927 --> 00:47:25,637
Like we’re being watched!

598
00:47:25,721 --> 00:47:27,556
Away put your weapon!

599
00:47:27,639 --> 00:47:29,641
I mean you no harm.

600
00:47:29,725 --> 00:47:32,686
I am wondering... why are you here?

601
00:47:32,769 --> 00:47:35,772
I’m looking for someone.

602
00:47:35,856 --> 00:47:37,316
Looking?

603
00:47:37,399 --> 00:47:40,068
Found someone you have,
I would say, hmmm?

604
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:42,863
Right.

605
00:47:42,946 --> 00:47:46,325
Help you I can. Yes, mmmm.

606
00:47:46,408 --> 00:47:48,410
I don’t think so.

607
00:47:48,493 --> 00:47:51,371
I’m looking for a great warrior.

608
00:47:51,455 --> 00:47:52,664
Ah!

609
00:47:52,748 --> 00:47:54,583
A great warrior.

610
00:47:54,666 --> 00:47:57,002
Ha ha ha!

611
00:47:57,085 --> 00:47:59,588
Wars not make one great.

612
00:48:07,554 --> 00:48:09,348
Put that down.

613
00:48:09,431 --> 00:48:11,934
Hey! That’s my dinner!

614
00:48:14,603 --> 00:48:17,856
How you get so big
eating food of this kind?

615
00:48:17,940 --> 00:48:20,025
Listen, friend, we didn’t mean
to land in that puddle.

616
00:48:20,108 --> 00:48:22,986
And if we could get our ship out, we would.
But we can’t, so why don’t you-

617
00:48:23,070 --> 00:48:24,988
Cannot get your ship out. Hee hee hee!

618
00:48:25,072 --> 00:48:26,532
Hey, get out of there!

619
00:48:26,615 --> 00:48:27,866
Ah!

620
00:48:27,950 --> 00:48:29,993
No! Ooh!

621
00:48:30,077 --> 00:48:32,538
Hey, you could have broken this.

622
00:48:32,621 --> 00:48:34,790
Don’t do that.

623
00:48:36,583 --> 00:48:38,001
Oh!

624
00:48:38,085 --> 00:48:39,795
[Chuckling]

625
00:48:42,464 --> 00:48:44,883
[Groaning]

626
00:48:44,967 --> 00:48:46,969
You’re making a mess.

627
00:48:47,970 --> 00:48:48,887
[Chuckling]

628
00:48:48,971 --> 00:48:50,848
Hey, give me that!

629
00:48:50,931 --> 00:48:53,559
Mine, or I will help you not.

630
00:48:53,642 --> 00:48:55,477
I don’t want your help. I want my lamp back.

631
00:48:55,561 --> 00:48:57,563
I’m gonna need it to get
out of this slimy mudhole.

632
00:48:57,646 --> 00:48:58,981
Mudhole? Slimy?

633
00:48:59,064 --> 00:49:01,775
My home this is-

634
00:49:01,859 --> 00:49:04,403
Wha-Mmm!

635
00:49:04,486 --> 00:49:06,029
R2, let him have it.

636
00:49:07,990 --> 00:49:10,450
Mine! Mine! Mine! Mine!

637
00:49:10,534 --> 00:49:11,618
R2!

638
00:49:13,912 --> 00:49:16,164
Now, will you move along, little fellow?

639
00:49:16,456 --> 00:49:17,916
We’ve got a lot of work to do.

640
00:49:17,999 --> 00:49:19,585
No! No, no!

641
00:49:19,668 --> 00:49:23,046
Stay and help you I will... find your friend.

642
00:49:23,130 --> 00:49:25,549
I’m not looking for a friend.

643
00:49:25,632 --> 00:49:26,842
I’m looking for a Jedi master.

644
00:49:26,925 --> 00:49:31,096
Oh. Jedi master. Yoda.

645
00:49:31,180 --> 00:49:32,806
You seek Yoda.

646
00:49:32,890 --> 00:49:34,016
You know him?

647
00:49:34,099 --> 00:49:37,603
Mmmm. Take you to him I will.

648
00:49:37,686 --> 00:49:42,191
Yes, yes, but now we must eat. Come.

649
00:49:42,482 --> 00:49:43,942
Good food.

650
00:49:44,026 --> 00:49:45,527
Come.

651
00:49:54,661 --> 00:49:56,538
Come, come.

652
00:49:57,873 --> 00:50:02,711
R2...stay and watch after the camp.

653
00:50:15,724 --> 00:50:18,477
Oh! Where is R2 when I need him?

654
00:50:18,560 --> 00:50:21,605
Sir, I don’t know where your ship
learned to communicate,

655
00:50:21,688 --> 00:50:23,482
but it has the most peculiar dialect.

656
00:50:23,565 --> 00:50:26,985
I believe, sir, it says that the power coupling
on the negative axis has been polarized.

657
00:50:27,069 --> 00:50:29,613
I’m afraid you’ll have to replace it.

658
00:50:29,696 --> 00:50:32,908
Well, of course I’ll have to replace it.

659
00:50:32,991 --> 00:50:34,576
Here!

660
00:50:34,660 --> 00:50:36,537
And, Chewie...

661
00:50:38,038 --> 00:50:40,791
I think we’d better replace
the negative power coupling.

662
00:51:01,854 --> 00:51:05,774
Hey, Your Worship,
I’m only trying to help.

663
00:51:05,858 --> 00:51:08,110
Would you please stop calling me that?

664
00:51:08,193 --> 00:51:10,279
Sure, Leia.

665
00:51:10,571 --> 00:51:12,573
You make it so difficult sometimes.

666
00:51:12,656 --> 00:51:14,616
I do. I really do.

667
00:51:14,700 --> 00:51:17,619
You could be a little nicer, though.

668
00:51:17,703 --> 00:51:20,622
Come on, admit it.
Sometimes you think I’m all right.

669
00:51:22,082 --> 00:51:24,585
Occasionally...maybe...

670
00:51:24,668 --> 00:51:27,129
when you aren’t acting like a scoundrel.

671
00:51:27,212 --> 00:51:29,047
Scoundrel?

672
00:51:29,131 --> 00:51:30,757
Scoundrel?

673
00:51:32,968 --> 00:51:35,554
I like the sound of that.

674
00:51:35,637 --> 00:51:36,555
Stop that.

675
00:51:36,638 --> 00:51:38,223
Stop what?

676
00:51:38,307 --> 00:51:40,559
Stop that. My hands are dirty.

677
00:51:40,642 --> 00:51:43,020
My hands are dirty, too.
What are you afraid of?

678
00:51:43,103 --> 00:51:44,229
Afraid?

679
00:51:44,313 --> 00:51:46,231
You’re trembling.

680
00:51:46,315 --> 00:51:48,025
I’m not trembling.

681
00:51:48,108 --> 00:51:52,237
You like me because I’m a scoundrel.

682
00:51:52,321 --> 00:51:54,573
There aren’t enough scoundrels in your life.

683
00:51:54,656 --> 00:51:57,034
I happen to like nice men.

684
00:51:57,117 --> 00:51:58,076
I’m a nice man.

685
00:51:58,160 --> 00:51:59,953
No, you’re not. You’re-

686
00:52:02,664 --> 00:52:03,749
Sir, sir!

687
00:52:03,832 --> 00:52:06,335
I’ve isolated the reverse
power flux coupling.

688
00:52:08,712 --> 00:52:09,922
Thank you.

689
00:52:10,005 --> 00:52:11,256
Thank you very much.

690
00:52:11,340 --> 00:52:13,175
Oh, you’re perfectly welcome, sir.

691
00:52:19,223 --> 00:52:22,601
And that was the last time
they appeared in any of our scopes.

692
00:52:22,684 --> 00:52:24,102
Considering the amount of damage we’ve sustained,

693
00:52:24,186 --> 00:52:25,604
they must have been destroyed.

694
00:52:25,687 --> 00:52:28,190
No, Captain. They’re alive.

695
00:52:28,273 --> 00:52:33,362
I want every ship available to sweep
the asteroid field until they are found.

696
00:52:37,282 --> 00:52:38,742
Lord Vader.

697
00:52:38,825 --> 00:52:40,744
Yes, Admiral. What is it?

698
00:52:40,827 --> 00:52:43,747
The emperor commands you
to make contact with him.

699
00:52:43,830 --> 00:52:48,669
Move the ship out of the asteroid field
so that we can send a clear transmission.

700
00:52:48,752 --> 00:52:50,170
Yes, my lord.

701
00:53:06,687 --> 00:53:09,147
What is thy bidding, my master?

702
00:53:10,274 --> 00:53:15,237
There is a great disturbance in the Force.

703
00:53:15,320 --> 00:53:17,781
I have felt it.

704
00:53:17,865 --> 00:53:20,325
We have a new enemy,

705
00:53:20,409 --> 00:53:24,413
the young rebel
who destroyed the Death Star.

706
00:53:24,705 --> 00:53:32,212
I have no doubt this boy
is the offspring of Anakin Skywalker.

707
00:53:32,296 --> 00:53:34,673
How is that possible?

708
00:53:34,756 --> 00:53:38,177
Search your feelings, Lord Vader.

709
00:53:38,260 --> 00:53:41,430
You will know it to be true.

710
00:53:41,680 --> 00:53:44,057
He could destroy us.

711
00:53:44,141 --> 00:53:46,268
He’s just a boy.

712
00:53:46,351 --> 00:53:48,896
Obi-Wan can no longer help him.

713
00:53:48,979 --> 00:53:52,733
The Force is strong with him.

714
00:53:53,942 --> 00:53:58,906
The son of Skywalker
must not become a Jedi.

715
00:53:58,989 --> 00:54:01,158
If he could be turned,

716
00:54:01,241 --> 00:54:04,119
he would become a powerful ally.

717
00:54:04,203 --> 00:54:06,872
Yes.

718
00:54:07,915 --> 00:54:12,044
He would be a great asset.

719
00:54:12,127 --> 00:54:14,379
Can it be done?

720
00:54:14,463 --> 00:54:18,425
He will join us or die, master.

721
00:54:35,108 --> 00:54:36,360
Look, I’m sure it’s delicious.

722
00:54:36,443 --> 00:54:39,321
I just don’t understand
why we can’t see Yoda now.

723
00:54:39,404 --> 00:54:40,405
Patience!

724
00:54:40,489 --> 00:54:41,949
For the Jedi,

725
00:54:42,032 --> 00:54:43,867
it is time to eat as well.

726
00:54:43,951 --> 00:54:45,869
Hmm? Heh heh.

727
00:54:45,953 --> 00:54:49,081
Eat, eat.

728
00:54:49,164 --> 00:54:50,249
Hot!

729
00:54:57,965 --> 00:55:00,008
Good food! Mmm, good, hmm?

730
00:55:00,092 --> 00:55:03,136
How far away is Yoda?
Will it take us long to get there?

731
00:55:03,220 --> 00:55:05,013
Not far. Yoda not far.

732
00:55:05,097 --> 00:55:08,225
Patience. Soon you will be with him.

733
00:55:10,811 --> 00:55:12,271
Root leaf.

734
00:55:12,354 --> 00:55:13,856
I cook.

735
00:55:13,939 --> 00:55:18,277
Why wish you become Jedi? Hmm? Hmm?

736
00:55:18,360 --> 00:55:20,445
Mostly because of my father, I guess.

737
00:55:20,529 --> 00:55:21,905
Ah, father.

738
00:55:21,989 --> 00:55:24,283
Powerful Jedi was he.

739
00:55:24,366 --> 00:55:26,285
Hee hee. Mmm, powerful Jedi.

740
00:55:26,368 --> 00:55:28,161
Oh, come on.

741
00:55:28,245 --> 00:55:29,788
How could you know my father?

742
00:55:29,872 --> 00:55:31,456
You don’t even know who I am.

743
00:55:31,540 --> 00:55:33,458
I don’t even know what I’m doing here.

744
00:55:33,542 --> 00:55:35,377
We’re wasting our time!

745
00:55:36,420 --> 00:55:38,297
I cannot teach him.

746
00:55:38,380 --> 00:55:40,924
The boy has no patience.

747
00:55:41,008 --> 00:55:43,468
<i>He will learn patience.</i>

748
00:55:43,552 --> 00:55:44,887
Hmm...

749
00:55:48,307 --> 00:55:50,893
Much anger in him,

750
00:55:50,976 --> 00:55:52,936
like his father.

751
00:55:53,020 --> 00:55:56,857
<i>Was I any different when you taught me?</i>

752
00:55:58,066 --> 00:55:59,943
No.

753
00:56:00,027 --> 00:56:01,862
He is not ready.

754
00:56:01,945 --> 00:56:03,238
Yoda.

755
00:56:05,365 --> 00:56:06,825
I am ready.

756
00:56:06,909 --> 00:56:09,161
Ben- I can be a Jedi.

757
00:56:09,244 --> 00:56:11,205
Ben, tell him I’m-

758
00:56:11,288 --> 00:56:12,831
Ready, are you?

759
00:56:12,915 --> 00:56:15,083
What know you ready?

760
00:56:15,167 --> 00:56:18,504
For 800 years have I trained Jedi.

761
00:56:18,587 --> 00:56:24,176
My own counsel will I keep
on who is to be trained.

762
00:56:24,259 --> 00:56:28,931
A Jedi must have the deepest commitment, hmm?

763
00:56:29,014 --> 00:56:30,933
The most serious mind.

764
00:56:32,518 --> 00:56:36,605
This one a long time have I watched.

765
00:56:36,855 --> 00:56:39,858
All his life has he looked away...

766
00:56:39,942 --> 00:56:43,028
to the future, to the horizon.

767
00:56:43,111 --> 00:56:46,532
Never his mind on where he was,

768
00:56:46,615 --> 00:56:47,866
hmm?

769
00:56:47,950 --> 00:56:49,910
What he was doing.

770
00:56:49,993 --> 00:56:51,453
Hmph!

771
00:56:51,537 --> 00:56:52,621
Adventure.

772
00:56:52,913 --> 00:56:53,914
Ha!

773
00:56:53,997 --> 00:56:55,332
Excitement. Ha!

774
00:56:55,415 --> 00:56:58,126
A Jedi craves not these things.

775
00:56:58,210 --> 00:57:00,921
You are reckless!

776
00:57:01,004 --> 00:57:04,007
<i>So was I, if you remember.</i>

777
00:57:04,091 --> 00:57:06,969
He is too old.

778
00:57:07,052 --> 00:57:09,638
Yes, too old to begin the training.

779
00:57:09,888 --> 00:57:12,349
But I’ve learned so much.

780
00:57:15,978 --> 00:57:17,229
Ahh...

781
00:57:18,647 --> 00:57:21,567
Will he finish what he begins?

782
00:57:21,650 --> 00:57:23,402
I won’t fail you.

783
00:57:24,987 --> 00:57:26,530
I’m not afraid.

784
00:57:28,156 --> 00:57:29,366
Oh...

785
00:57:30,993 --> 00:57:32,995
You will be.

786
00:57:34,288 --> 00:57:36,373
You will be.

787
00:58:15,537 --> 00:58:17,039
[Squealing]

788
00:58:17,122 --> 00:58:18,332
Aah!

789
00:58:18,415 --> 00:58:20,334
Sir, if I may venture an opinion-

790
00:58:20,417 --> 00:58:22,377
I’m not really interested in your opinion.

791
00:58:22,461 --> 00:58:23,712
There’s something out there.

792
00:58:24,004 --> 00:58:25,130
Where?

793
00:58:25,214 --> 00:58:26,215
Outside in the cave.

794
00:58:26,298 --> 00:58:27,716
[Banging]

795
00:58:27,966 --> 00:58:29,218
There it is. Listen. Listen!

796
00:58:29,301 --> 00:58:30,344
I’m going out there.

797
00:58:30,427 --> 00:58:31,428
Are you crazy?

798
00:58:31,512 --> 00:58:32,971
I just got this bucket back together.

799
00:58:33,055 --> 00:58:35,098
I’m not going to let something tear it apart.

800
00:58:35,182 --> 00:58:36,975
Then I’m going with you.

801
00:58:37,059 --> 00:58:38,519
I think it might be better

802
00:58:38,602 --> 00:58:40,646
[Roar]
if I stay behind and guard the ship.

803
00:58:40,729 --> 00:58:41,730
Oh, no.

804
00:58:55,661 --> 00:58:59,039
This ground sure feels strange.

805
00:58:59,122 --> 00:59:01,542
It doesn’t feel like rock.

806
00:59:05,087 --> 00:59:08,465
There’s an awful lot of moisture in here.

807
00:59:08,549 --> 00:59:10,384
I don’t know.

808
00:59:10,467 --> 00:59:13,512
I have a bad feeling about this.

809
00:59:13,595 --> 00:59:14,680
Yeah.

810
00:59:16,431 --> 00:59:17,391
Watch out!

811
00:59:18,517 --> 00:59:19,768
It’s all right.

812
00:59:20,018 --> 00:59:21,019
It’s all right.

813
00:59:21,103 --> 00:59:23,021
Yeah, that’s what I thought-mynock.

814
00:59:23,105 --> 00:59:27,317
Chewie, check the rest of the ship
and make sure there are no more attached,

815
00:59:27,401 --> 00:59:29,528
chewing on the power cables.

816
00:59:29,611 --> 00:59:31,071
Mynocks.

817
00:59:31,154 --> 00:59:33,365
Go on inside.
We’ll clean them off if there are any more.

818
00:59:37,786 --> 00:59:39,538
Han!

819
00:59:41,248 --> 00:59:43,792
Aagghh! Go away, go away, beastly thing!

820
00:59:44,042 --> 00:59:45,127
Shoo! Shoo!

821
00:59:51,758 --> 00:59:53,677
Wait a minute...

822
01:00:15,490 --> 01:00:16,742
Let’s get out of here!

823
01:00:16,825 --> 01:00:19,161
The Empire is still out there!
I don’t think-

824
01:00:19,244 --> 01:00:21,413
No time to discuss this in committee!

825
01:00:21,496 --> 01:00:23,498
I’m not a committee!

826
01:00:29,505 --> 01:00:32,424
You can’t make the jump
to light speed in this asteroid field.

827
01:00:32,508 --> 01:00:35,260
Sit down, sweetheart! We’re taking off!

828
01:00:39,097 --> 01:00:40,098
Look!

829
01:00:40,182 --> 01:00:41,391
I see it. I see it.

830
01:00:41,475 --> 01:00:42,434
We’re doomed!

831
01:00:42,518 --> 01:00:43,769
The cave is collapsing.

832
01:00:43,852 --> 01:00:45,854
This is no cave.
What?

833
01:01:18,679 --> 01:01:19,680
Run!

834
01:01:19,763 --> 01:01:23,642
Yes! A Jedi’s strength flows from the Force.

835
01:01:23,725 --> 01:01:26,436
But beware of the dark side.

836
01:01:26,520 --> 01:01:28,230
Anger, fear, aggression-

837
01:01:28,313 --> 01:01:31,400
The dark side of the Force are they,

838
01:01:31,483 --> 01:01:34,403
easily they flow,
quick to join you in a fight.

839
01:01:34,486 --> 01:01:37,281
If once you start down the dark path,

840
01:01:37,364 --> 01:01:39,408
forever will it dominate your destiny.

841
01:01:39,491 --> 01:01:40,826
Consume you it will,

842
01:01:40,909 --> 01:01:42,744
as it did Obi-Wan’s apprentice.

843
01:01:42,828 --> 01:01:44,329
Vader.

844
01:01:44,413 --> 01:01:46,623
Is the dark side stronger?

845
01:01:46,707 --> 01:01:48,208
No, no.

846
01:01:48,292 --> 01:01:49,585
No.

847
01:01:49,668 --> 01:01:52,212
Quicker, easier, more seductive.

848
01:01:52,296 --> 01:01:55,174
How do I know
the good side from the bad?

849
01:01:55,257 --> 01:01:58,427
You will know when you are calm,

850
01:01:58,510 --> 01:02:00,429
at peace,

851
01:02:00,512 --> 01:02:02,222
passive.

852
01:02:02,306 --> 01:02:07,352
A Jedi uses the Force
for knowledge and defense,

853
01:02:07,436 --> 01:02:09,563
never for attack.

854
01:02:09,646 --> 01:02:10,647
But tell me why I can’t-

855
01:02:10,731 --> 01:02:12,774
No, no. There is no why.

856
01:02:12,858 --> 01:02:15,652
Nothing more will I teach you today.

857
01:02:15,736 --> 01:02:18,363
Clear your mind of questions.

858
01:02:18,447 --> 01:02:22,201
Hmm...

859
01:02:22,284 --> 01:02:23,785
Mmm...

860
01:02:40,636 --> 01:02:42,763
There’s something not right here.

861
01:02:46,475 --> 01:02:48,644
I feel cold...

862
01:02:48,727 --> 01:02:49,811
death.

863
01:02:49,895 --> 01:02:51,980
That place...

864
01:02:52,272 --> 01:02:55,400
is strong with the dark side of the Force.

865
01:02:55,484 --> 01:02:57,736
A domain of evil it is.

866
01:02:59,488 --> 01:03:01,240
In you must go.

867
01:03:01,323 --> 01:03:03,575
What’s in there?

868
01:03:05,536 --> 01:03:07,579
Only what you take with you.

869
01:03:11,834 --> 01:03:13,585
Your weapons...

870
01:03:13,669 --> 01:03:15,879
you will not need them.

871
01:03:28,725 --> 01:03:29,810
[Squish]

872
01:03:29,893 --> 01:03:32,479
[Screeching]

873
01:04:14,771 --> 01:04:16,607
[Aaaar]

874
01:05:37,604 --> 01:05:40,566
<i>[Blip Blip Beep Beep]</i>

875
01:05:44,486 --> 01:05:45,487
Hmph...

876
01:05:55,497 --> 01:05:56,456
Bounty hunters.

877
01:05:56,540 --> 01:05:57,875
We don’t need their scum.

878
01:05:57,958 --> 01:05:59,459
Yes, sir.

879
01:05:59,543 --> 01:06:01,628
Those rebels won’t escape us.

880
01:06:03,422 --> 01:06:05,174
[Speaking Alien Language]

881
01:06:07,134 --> 01:06:11,597
<i>Sir, we have a priority signal</i>
<i>from the Stardestroyer Avenger.</i>

882
01:06:11,680 --> 01:06:18,645
<i>There will be a substantial reward</i>
<i>for the one who finds the Millennium Falcon.</i>

883
01:06:18,729 --> 01:06:21,190
You are free to use any methods necessary,

884
01:06:21,481 --> 01:06:23,609
but I want them alive.

885
01:06:23,692 --> 01:06:26,028
No disintegrations.

886
01:06:26,111 --> 01:06:27,988
As you wish.

887
01:06:28,071 --> 01:06:29,448
Lord Vader.

888
01:06:29,531 --> 01:06:32,075
My lord, we have them.

889
01:06:36,705 --> 01:06:39,833
Oh, thank goodness
we’re coming out of the asteroid field.

890
01:06:43,545 --> 01:06:45,464
Let’s get out of here.

891
01:06:45,547 --> 01:06:46,882
Ready for light speed?

892
01:06:46,965 --> 01:06:48,133
1...

893
01:06:48,217 --> 01:06:49,968
2...

894
01:06:50,052 --> 01:06:51,220
3!

895
01:06:57,226 --> 01:06:58,644
It’s not fair.

896
01:06:58,727 --> 01:07:00,062
Gahhh!

897
01:07:00,145 --> 01:07:02,481
Transfer circuits aren’t working.

898
01:07:02,564 --> 01:07:04,566
It’s not my fault!

899
01:07:04,650 --> 01:07:05,651
No light speed?

900
01:07:05,734 --> 01:07:07,653
It’s not my fault.

901
01:07:12,241 --> 01:07:14,243
Sir, we’ve just lost
the main rear deflector shield.

902
01:07:14,535 --> 01:07:16,745
One more direct hit
on the back quarter and we’re done for.

903
01:07:16,828 --> 01:07:18,622
Turn her around.

904
01:07:18,705 --> 01:07:20,832
I’m going to put all power
in the front shield.

905
01:07:20,916 --> 01:07:22,167
You’re going to attack them?

906
01:07:22,251 --> 01:07:25,546
Sir, the odds of surviving
a direct assault on an imperial-

907
01:07:25,629 --> 01:07:27,589
Shut up!
Gaahh!

908
01:07:33,971 --> 01:07:35,973
They’re moving to attack position.

909
01:07:38,100 --> 01:07:39,268
Shields up.

910
01:07:43,981 --> 01:07:45,274
Track them.

911
01:07:45,566 --> 01:07:47,609
They may come around for another pass.

912
01:07:47,693 --> 01:07:50,028
Captain Needa, the ship
no longer appears on our scopes.

913
01:07:50,112 --> 01:07:52,030
They can’t have disappeared.

914
01:07:52,114 --> 01:07:54,741
No ship that small has a cloaking device.

915
01:07:54,825 --> 01:07:56,702
Well, there’s no trace of them, sir.

916
01:07:56,785 --> 01:07:58,745
Captain, Lord Vader
demands an update on the pursuit.

917
01:08:01,123 --> 01:08:02,875
Get a shuttle ready.

918
01:08:02,958 --> 01:08:07,212
I shall assume full responsibility for losing them
and apologize to Lord Vader.

919
01:08:07,296 --> 01:08:09,214
Meanwhile, continue to scan the area.

920
01:08:09,298 --> 01:08:10,966
Yes, Captain Needa.

921
01:08:15,721 --> 01:08:17,973
Use the Force.

922
01:08:18,056 --> 01:08:19,057
Yes.

923
01:08:24,730 --> 01:08:26,315
Now, the stone...

924
01:08:29,943 --> 01:08:31,987
Feel it.

925
01:08:35,991 --> 01:08:37,826
<i>[Blip Blip Beep Beep Blip]</i>

926
01:08:43,957 --> 01:08:45,834
Concentrate!

927
01:08:59,973 --> 01:09:03,602
Oh, no. We’ll never get it out now.

928
01:09:03,685 --> 01:09:05,312
So certain are you.

929
01:09:07,356 --> 01:09:08,899
[Sighs]

930
01:09:08,982 --> 01:09:12,069
Always with you it cannot be done.

931
01:09:13,862 --> 01:09:15,864
Hear you nothing that I say?

932
01:09:15,948 --> 01:09:18,283
Master, moving stones around is one thing.

933
01:09:18,367 --> 01:09:19,993
This is totally different.

934
01:09:20,077 --> 01:09:21,745
No! No different!

935
01:09:21,828 --> 01:09:24,122
Only different in your mind.

936
01:09:24,206 --> 01:09:27,960
You must unlearn what you have learned.

937
01:09:28,043 --> 01:09:30,629
All right. I’ll give it a try.

938
01:09:30,712 --> 01:09:32,297
No! Try not.

939
01:09:32,381 --> 01:09:34,758
Do.

940
01:09:34,842 --> 01:09:36,093
Or do not.

941
01:09:36,176 --> 01:09:38,220
There is no try.

942
01:09:58,657 --> 01:10:00,409
<i>[Blip Blip Beep Beep]</i>

943
01:10:25,767 --> 01:10:28,687
I can’t. It’s too big.

944
01:10:28,770 --> 01:10:31,690
Size matters not. Look at me.

945
01:10:31,773 --> 01:10:35,027
Judge me by my size, do you?

946
01:10:35,110 --> 01:10:36,111
Hmm?

947
01:10:36,195 --> 01:10:37,738
Hmph!

948
01:10:37,821 --> 01:10:39,990
And well you should not,

949
01:10:40,073 --> 01:10:43,202
for my ally is the Force.

950
01:10:43,285 --> 01:10:46,205
And a powerful ally it is.

951
01:10:46,288 --> 01:10:48,457
Life creates it,

952
01:10:48,749 --> 01:10:50,250
makes it grow.

953
01:10:51,460 --> 01:10:55,214
Its energy surrounds us...

954
01:10:55,297 --> 01:10:57,216
and binds us.

955
01:10:57,299 --> 01:10:59,468
Luminous beings are we,

956
01:10:59,718 --> 01:11:01,470
not this crude matter.

957
01:11:01,720 --> 01:11:05,807
You must feel the Force around you-

958
01:11:05,891 --> 01:11:09,186
Here, between you, me,

959
01:11:09,269 --> 01:11:13,106
the tree, the rock, everywhere!

960
01:11:13,190 --> 01:11:14,483
Yes...

961
01:11:16,151 --> 01:11:20,072
Even between the land and the ship.

962
01:11:24,076 --> 01:11:26,078
You want the impossible.

963
01:11:56,400 --> 01:11:59,361
<i>[Beep Blip Beep Beep]</i>

964
01:13:00,506 --> 01:13:02,424
Mm...

965
01:13:13,477 --> 01:13:14,478
I don’t...

966
01:13:14,561 --> 01:13:16,897
I don’t believe it.

967
01:13:17,940 --> 01:13:21,193
That is why you fail.

968
01:13:39,878 --> 01:13:43,966
Apology accepted, Captain Needa.

969
01:13:51,473 --> 01:13:55,143
Lord Vader, our ships have completed
their scan of the area and found nothing.

970
01:13:55,227 --> 01:13:59,565
<i>If the Millennium Falcon went into light speed</i>
<i>it’ll be on the other side of the galaxy by now.</i>

971
01:13:59,648 --> 01:14:00,649
Alert all commands.

972
01:14:00,899 --> 01:14:06,029
Calculate every possible destination
along their last known trajectory.

973
01:14:06,113 --> 01:14:07,364
Yes, my lord. We’ll find them.

974
01:14:07,447 --> 01:14:09,491
Don’t fail me again...

975
01:14:10,492 --> 01:14:11,577
Admiral.

976
01:14:13,161 --> 01:14:15,080
Alert all commands.

977
01:14:15,163 --> 01:14:17,124
Deploy the fleet.

978
01:14:32,097 --> 01:14:34,308
Captain Solo,
this time you’ve gone too far.

979
01:14:34,391 --> 01:14:35,684
Gahhh!

980
01:14:35,976 --> 01:14:38,437
I will not be quiet.
Why doesn’t anyone listen to me?

981
01:14:38,520 --> 01:14:40,439
The fleet’s beginning to break up.

982
01:14:40,522 --> 01:14:44,610
Go back and stand by
the manual release for the landing claw.

983
01:14:47,070 --> 01:14:49,072
I really don’t see how that’s going to help.

984
01:14:49,156 --> 01:14:52,326
Surrender is a perfectly acceptable alternative
in extreme circumstances.

985
01:14:52,409 --> 01:14:54,286
The Empire may be gracious enough-

986
01:14:54,369 --> 01:14:55,329
Thank you.

987
01:14:55,412 --> 01:14:57,164
What’s your next move?

988
01:14:57,247 --> 01:14:58,582
If they follow standard imperial procedure,

989
01:14:58,665 --> 01:15:01,627
they’ll dump their garbage
before they go to light speed,

990
01:15:01,710 --> 01:15:03,212
and then we just float away.

991
01:15:03,295 --> 01:15:04,963
With the rest of the garbage.

992
01:15:05,047 --> 01:15:06,298
Then what?

993
01:15:06,381 --> 01:15:09,134
Then we got to find a safe port
somewhere around here.

994
01:15:09,218 --> 01:15:10,219
Any ideas?

995
01:15:10,302 --> 01:15:11,637
Where are we?

996
01:15:11,720 --> 01:15:13,222
The Anoat system.

997
01:15:13,305 --> 01:15:15,224
There’s not much there.

998
01:15:15,307 --> 01:15:19,186
No. Well, wait. This is interesting.

999
01:15:19,269 --> 01:15:20,354
Lando.

1000
01:15:20,437 --> 01:15:21,980
Lando system?

1001
01:15:22,064 --> 01:15:24,983
Lando’s not a system.
He’s a man. Lando Calrissian.

1002
01:15:25,067 --> 01:15:27,361
He’s a cardplayer, gambler, scoundrel.

1003
01:15:27,444 --> 01:15:28,654
You’d like him.

1004
01:15:28,737 --> 01:15:30,239
Thanks.

1005
01:15:30,322 --> 01:15:34,076
Bespin. It’s pretty far,
but I think we can make it.

1006
01:15:34,159 --> 01:15:36,119
A mining colony?

1007
01:15:36,203 --> 01:15:38,497
Yeah, a tibanna gas mine.

1008
01:15:38,580 --> 01:15:41,500
Lando conned somebody out of it.

1009
01:15:41,583 --> 01:15:44,419
We go back a long way,
Lando and me.

1010
01:15:44,503 --> 01:15:46,463
Can you trust him?

1011
01:15:46,547 --> 01:15:49,758
No. But he’s got no love for the Empire,

1012
01:15:50,008 --> 01:15:51,343
I can tell you that.

1013
01:15:51,426 --> 01:15:54,012
Here we go, Chewie. Stand by.

1014
01:15:54,096 --> 01:15:55,180
Detach.

1015
01:16:01,687 --> 01:16:03,772
You do have your moments.

1016
01:16:04,022 --> 01:16:05,691
Not many of them,

1017
01:16:05,774 --> 01:16:08,318
but you do have them.

1018
01:16:39,474 --> 01:16:41,226
<i>[Beep Beep Blip Blip]</i>

1019
01:16:41,310 --> 01:16:43,729
Concentrate.

1020
01:16:43,812 --> 01:16:47,107
Feel the Force flow.

1021
01:16:47,191 --> 01:16:49,359
Yes.

1022
01:16:49,443 --> 01:16:51,445
<i>[Blip Blip Beep]</i>

1023
01:16:51,528 --> 01:16:52,738
<i>[Beep]</i>

1024
01:16:52,821 --> 01:16:55,115
<i>[Blip Blip]</i>

1025
01:16:56,325 --> 01:16:57,743
Good.

1026
01:16:57,826 --> 01:16:59,328
Calm.

1027
01:16:59,411 --> 01:17:01,580
Yes.

1028
01:17:01,663 --> 01:17:05,125
Through the Force, things you will see.

1029
01:17:05,209 --> 01:17:08,670
Other places. The future. The past.

1030
01:17:08,754 --> 01:17:11,340
Old friends long gone.

1031
01:17:13,592 --> 01:17:14,843
Han?

1032
01:17:15,093 --> 01:17:17,346
Leia!

1033
01:17:17,429 --> 01:17:18,514
<i>[Eee!]</i>

1034
01:17:19,848 --> 01:17:21,683
Hmm...

1035
01:17:21,767 --> 01:17:23,268
Control, control.

1036
01:17:23,352 --> 01:17:25,270
You must learn control!

1037
01:17:25,354 --> 01:17:27,231
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

1038
01:17:27,314 --> 01:17:31,527
I saw...I saw a city in the clouds.

1039
01:17:31,610 --> 01:17:33,153
Hmm...

1040
01:17:33,237 --> 01:17:35,739
Friends you have there.

1041
01:17:35,822 --> 01:17:37,783
They were in pain.

1042
01:17:37,866 --> 01:17:41,328
It is the future you see.

1043
01:17:41,411 --> 01:17:42,704
Future?

1044
01:17:51,296 --> 01:17:53,215
Will they die?

1045
01:17:56,134 --> 01:17:57,636
Difficult to see.

1046
01:17:57,719 --> 01:18:01,223
Always in motion is the future.

1047
01:18:02,224 --> 01:18:04,893
I’ve got to go to them.

1048
01:18:06,478 --> 01:18:09,398
Decide you must how to serve them best.

1049
01:18:09,481 --> 01:18:12,276
If you leave now, help them you could,

1050
01:18:12,359 --> 01:18:17,656
but you would destroy all
for which they have fought and suffered.

1051
01:18:30,794 --> 01:18:34,339
No, I don’t have a landing permit.

1052
01:18:34,423 --> 01:18:38,343
I’m trying to reach Lando Calrissian.

1053
01:18:38,427 --> 01:18:40,512
Wait a minute! Let me explain!

1054
01:18:40,596 --> 01:18:41,930
<i>You will not deviate from your present course.</i>

1055
01:18:42,222 --> 01:18:43,682
Rather touchy, aren’t they?

1056
01:18:43,765 --> 01:18:45,475
I thought you knew this person.

1057
01:18:45,559 --> 01:18:47,477
Gaah!

1058
01:18:47,561 --> 01:18:49,396
That was a long time ago.

1059
01:18:49,479 --> 01:18:51,273
I’m sure he’s forgotten about that.

1060
01:18:58,697 --> 01:19:03,410
<i>Permission granted to land</i>
<i>on Platform 3-2-7.</i>

1061
01:19:03,493 --> 01:19:04,870
Thank you.

1062
01:19:04,953 --> 01:19:06,872
Nothing to worry about.

1063
01:19:06,955 --> 01:19:08,665
We go way back, Lando and me.

1064
01:19:08,749 --> 01:19:10,542
Who’s worried?

1065
01:19:58,257 --> 01:20:00,717
Oh. No one to meet us.

1066
01:20:00,801 --> 01:20:02,719
I don’t like this.

1067
01:20:02,803 --> 01:20:05,305
Well, what would you like?

1068
01:20:05,389 --> 01:20:07,724
<i>They did let us land.</i>

1069
01:20:07,808 --> 01:20:09,726
Look, don’t worry.
Everything’s going to be fine.

1070
01:20:09,810 --> 01:20:11,353
Trust me.

1071
01:20:15,858 --> 01:20:18,318
See? My friend.

1072
01:20:22,489 --> 01:20:24,950
Keep your eyes open, huh?

1073
01:20:25,033 --> 01:20:26,952
Gahhh!

1074
01:20:27,035 --> 01:20:28,620
Hey!

1075
01:20:28,704 --> 01:20:30,455
Why, you slimy,

1076
01:20:30,539 --> 01:20:33,792
double-crossing, no-good swindler.

1077
01:20:33,876 --> 01:20:38,338
You’ve got a lot of guts coming here
after what you pulled.

1078
01:20:45,971 --> 01:20:48,599
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!

1079
01:20:48,682 --> 01:20:52,060
How you doin’, you old pirate?
So good to see you!

1080
01:20:52,352 --> 01:20:55,397
Well, he seems very friendly.

1081
01:20:55,480 --> 01:20:56,440
Yes.

1082
01:20:56,523 --> 01:20:58,567
Very friendly.

1083
01:20:58,650 --> 01:20:59,943
What are you doing here?

1084
01:21:00,027 --> 01:21:02,487
Ah, repairs.
I thought you could help me out.

1085
01:21:02,571 --> 01:21:04,531
What have you done to my ship?

1086
01:21:04,615 --> 01:21:05,574
Your ship?

1087
01:21:05,657 --> 01:21:06,658
Hey, remember,

1088
01:21:06,742 --> 01:21:08,827
you lost her to me fair and square.

1089
01:21:08,911 --> 01:21:10,996
And how you doin’, Chewbacca?

1090
01:21:11,079 --> 01:21:12,372
Gahh!

1091
01:21:12,456 --> 01:21:13,790
You still hanging around
with this loser?

1092
01:21:13,874 --> 01:21:16,627
Gahhh!

1093
01:21:16,710 --> 01:21:19,004
Hello. What have we here?

1094
01:21:19,087 --> 01:21:20,506
Welcome, I’m Lando Calrissian.

1095
01:21:20,589 --> 01:21:23,383
I’m the administrator of this facility.

1096
01:21:23,467 --> 01:21:25,385
And who might you be?

1097
01:21:25,469 --> 01:21:26,553
Leia.

1098
01:21:26,637 --> 01:21:28,096
Welcome, Leia.

1099
01:21:31,433 --> 01:21:34,728
All right, all right, you old smoothie.

1100
01:21:34,811 --> 01:21:38,357
Hello, sir. I am C-3PO, human-cyborg relations.

1101
01:21:38,440 --> 01:21:39,775
My facilities are at your-

1102
01:21:39,858 --> 01:21:41,360
Well, really!

1103
01:21:41,443 --> 01:21:43,111
<i>What’s wrong with the Falcon?</i>

1104
01:21:43,362 --> 01:21:44,530
Hyperdrive.

1105
01:21:44,613 --> 01:21:46,532
I’ll get my people to work on her.

1106
01:21:46,615 --> 01:21:48,367
That ship saved my life quite a few times.

1107
01:21:48,450 --> 01:21:51,370
She’s the fastest
hunk of junk in the galaxy.

1108
01:21:51,453 --> 01:21:54,581
How’s the gas mine?
Still paying off for you?

1109
01:21:54,665 --> 01:21:55,916
Not as well as I’d like.

1110
01:21:55,999 --> 01:21:58,377
We’re a small outpost
and not very self-sufficient.

1111
01:21:58,460 --> 01:21:59,753
I’ve had supply problems of every kind.

1112
01:21:59,837 --> 01:22:01,380
I’ve had labor difficulties.

1113
01:22:01,463 --> 01:22:02,923
Ha ha ha!

1114
01:22:03,006 --> 01:22:04,675
What’s so funny?

1115
01:22:04,758 --> 01:22:06,385
You. Listen to you.

1116
01:22:06,468 --> 01:22:08,512
You sound like a businessman,

1117
01:22:08,595 --> 01:22:09,888
a responsible leader.

1118
01:22:09,972 --> 01:22:12,140
Who’d have thought that, huh?

1119
01:22:12,391 --> 01:22:14,852
Seeing you brings back a few things.

1120
01:22:14,935 --> 01:22:15,978
Yeah.

1121
01:22:16,061 --> 01:22:17,896
Yeah, I’m responsible these days.

1122
01:22:17,980 --> 01:22:21,984
It’s the price you pay for being successful.

1123
01:22:24,403 --> 01:22:26,780
Ooh. Nice to see a familiar face.

1124
01:22:26,864 --> 01:22:28,407
<i>E chu ta!</i>

1125
01:22:28,490 --> 01:22:29,783
How rude!

1126
01:22:29,867 --> 01:22:31,410
<i>[Beep Beep]</i>

1127
01:22:31,493 --> 01:22:33,412
That sounds like an R2 unit in there.

1128
01:22:33,495 --> 01:22:34,872
I wonder if-Hello?

1129
01:22:36,665 --> 01:22:37,958
How interesting.

1130
01:22:38,041 --> 01:22:39,751
Who are you?

1131
01:22:39,835 --> 01:22:41,170
Oh, my! I- I’m terribly sorry.

1132
01:22:41,420 --> 01:22:42,796
I didn’t mean to intrude.

1133
01:22:42,880 --> 01:22:44,006
No, please don’t get up.

1134
01:22:50,596 --> 01:22:51,930
Gahhh.

1135
01:23:02,566 --> 01:23:05,068
Luke, you must complete the training.

1136
01:23:05,152 --> 01:23:06,820
I can’t keep the vision out of my head.

1137
01:23:06,904 --> 01:23:08,947
They’re my friends. I got to help them.

1138
01:23:09,031 --> 01:23:11,200
You must not go.

1139
01:23:11,450 --> 01:23:14,536
But Han and Leia will die if I don’t.

1140
01:23:14,620 --> 01:23:16,038
<i>You don’t know that.</i>

1141
01:23:16,121 --> 01:23:18,999
<i>Even Yoda cannot see their fate.</i>

1142
01:23:19,082 --> 01:23:21,460
But I can help them.

1143
01:23:21,543 --> 01:23:22,878
I feel the Force.

1144
01:23:22,961 --> 01:23:24,546
<i>But you cannot control it.</i>

1145
01:23:24,630 --> 01:23:27,049
<i>This is a dangerous time for you,</i>

1146
01:23:27,132 --> 01:23:30,969
<i>when you will be tempted</i>
<i>by the dark side of the Force.</i>

1147
01:23:31,053 --> 01:23:34,223
Yes! Yes! To Obi-Wan you listen.

1148
01:23:34,515 --> 01:23:37,518
The cave. Remember your failure at the cave.

1149
01:23:37,601 --> 01:23:40,854
But I’ve learned so much since then.

1150
01:23:40,938 --> 01:23:44,233
Master Yoda, I promise to return
and to finish what I’ve begun.

1151
01:23:44,525 --> 01:23:45,776
You have my word.

1152
01:23:45,859 --> 01:23:48,654
<i>It is you and your abilities</i>
<i>the emperor wants.</i>

1153
01:23:48,737 --> 01:23:52,616
<i>That is why your friends are made to suffer.</i>

1154
01:23:52,699 --> 01:23:54,660
That’s why I have to go.

1155
01:23:54,743 --> 01:24:00,040
<i>Luke, I don’t want to lose you to the emperor</i>
<i>the way I lost Vader.</i>

1156
01:24:00,123 --> 01:24:01,750
You won’t.

1157
01:24:01,834 --> 01:24:03,752
Stopped they must be.

1158
01:24:03,836 --> 01:24:06,129
On this all depends.

1159
01:24:06,213 --> 01:24:08,674
Only a fully trained Jedi knight,

1160
01:24:08,757 --> 01:24:10,592
with the Force as his ally,

1161
01:24:10,676 --> 01:24:13,178
will conquer Vader and his emperor.

1162
01:24:13,262 --> 01:24:15,514
If you end your training now,

1163
01:24:15,597 --> 01:24:19,852
if you choose the quick
and easy path, as Vader did,

1164
01:24:19,935 --> 01:24:22,688
you will become an agent of evil.

1165
01:24:22,771 --> 01:24:23,730
<i>Patience.</i>

1166
01:24:23,814 --> 01:24:25,983
And sacrifice Han and Leia?

1167
01:24:26,066 --> 01:24:30,112
If you honor what they fight for...yes.

1168
01:24:30,195 --> 01:24:31,905
<i>If you choose to face Vader,</i>

1169
01:24:31,989 --> 01:24:33,282
<i>you will do it alone.</i>

1170
01:24:33,574 --> 01:24:35,617
<i>I cannot interfere.</i>

1171
01:24:36,785 --> 01:24:38,871
I understand.

1172
01:24:43,292 --> 01:24:44,668
R2.

1173
01:24:44,751 --> 01:24:46,044
<i>[Blip Beep]</i>

1174
01:24:46,128 --> 01:24:48,046
Fire up the converters.

1175
01:24:50,174 --> 01:24:51,216
<i>Luke!</i>

1176
01:24:51,300 --> 01:24:54,553
<i>Don’t give in to hate.</i>

1177
01:24:54,636 --> 01:24:57,222
<i>That leads to the dark side.</i>

1178
01:24:57,306 --> 01:24:58,807
Strong is Vader.

1179
01:24:58,891 --> 01:25:01,810
Mind what you have learned. Save you it can.

1180
01:25:01,894 --> 01:25:03,228
I will.

1181
01:25:03,312 --> 01:25:05,063
And I’ll return.

1182
01:25:05,147 --> 01:25:06,732
I promise.

1183
01:25:13,322 --> 01:25:15,240
Told you, I did.

1184
01:25:15,324 --> 01:25:17,075
Reckless is he.

1185
01:25:17,159 --> 01:25:18,243
Now...

1186
01:25:18,327 --> 01:25:20,120
matters are worse.

1187
01:25:20,204 --> 01:25:23,123
<i>That boy is our last hope.</i>

1188
01:25:23,207 --> 01:25:25,292
No, there is another.

1189
01:25:57,115 --> 01:25:58,617
The ship’s almost finished.

1190
01:25:58,700 --> 01:26:00,869
Two or three more things
and we’re in great shape.

1191
01:26:00,953 --> 01:26:02,621
The sooner the better. Something is wrong here.

1192
01:26:02,704 --> 01:26:05,123
No one has seen or knows anything about 3PO.

1193
01:26:05,207 --> 01:26:07,626
He’s been gone too long to have gotten lost.

1194
01:26:07,709 --> 01:26:12,631
Relax. I’ll talk to Lando
and see what I can find out.

1195
01:26:12,714 --> 01:26:14,633
I don’t trust Lando.

1196
01:26:14,716 --> 01:26:17,052
Well, I don’t trust him either.

1197
01:26:17,135 --> 01:26:19,763
But he is my friend. Besides...

1198
01:26:19,847 --> 01:26:21,723
we’ll soon be gone.

1199
01:26:21,807 --> 01:26:25,060
Then you’re as good as gone,
aren’t you?

1200
01:26:58,260 --> 01:26:59,803
Gaahh!

1201
01:26:59,887 --> 01:27:00,929
What happened?

1202
01:27:01,013 --> 01:27:02,681
Gahhh gahhh.

1203
01:27:02,764 --> 01:27:03,974
Where?

1204
01:27:04,057 --> 01:27:05,350
Gahhh!

1205
01:27:05,434 --> 01:27:07,269
Found him in a junk pile?

1206
01:27:07,352 --> 01:27:10,189
Oh, what a mess.
Chewie, you think you can repair him?

1207
01:27:10,272 --> 01:27:12,191
Gahhh!

1208
01:27:12,274 --> 01:27:14,026
Lando’s got people that can fix him.

1209
01:27:14,109 --> 01:27:15,444
No, thanks.

1210
01:27:15,736 --> 01:27:19,239
I’m sorry, am I interrupting anything?

1211
01:27:19,323 --> 01:27:21,283
Not really.

1212
01:27:24,870 --> 01:27:26,955
You look absolutely beautiful.

1213
01:27:27,039 --> 01:27:30,292
You truly belong here with us among the clouds.

1214
01:27:30,375 --> 01:27:31,877
Thank you.

1215
01:27:31,960 --> 01:27:34,880
Would you join me for a little refreshment?

1216
01:27:34,963 --> 01:27:36,465
Everyone’s invited, of course.

1217
01:27:38,008 --> 01:27:39,885
Having trouble with your droid?

1218
01:27:39,968 --> 01:27:41,303
No, no problem.

1219
01:27:41,386 --> 01:27:42,429
Why?

1220
01:27:50,729 --> 01:27:52,981
You see, since we’re a small operation,

1221
01:27:53,065 --> 01:27:57,402
we don’t fall into
the jurisdiction of the Empire.

1222
01:27:57,486 --> 01:27:59,112
So you’re part of the Mining Guild, then?

1223
01:27:59,196 --> 01:28:02,407
No, not actually. Our operation
is small enough not to be noticed.

1224
01:28:02,491 --> 01:28:04,409
Which is advantageous for everybody,

1225
01:28:04,493 --> 01:28:09,248
since our customers are anxious
to avoid attracting attention to themselves.

1226
01:28:09,331 --> 01:28:13,752
Aren’t you afraid the Empire’s going to find out
about this little operation, shut you down?

1227
01:28:13,836 --> 01:28:16,171
It’s always been a danger that looms
like a shadow over everything we’ve built.

1228
01:28:16,255 --> 01:28:18,757
But things have developed
that’ll ensure security.

1229
01:28:18,841 --> 01:28:23,804
I’ve just made a deal
that will keep the Empire out of here forever.

1230
01:28:32,521 --> 01:28:35,399
We would be honored if you would join us.

1231
01:28:40,946 --> 01:28:42,281
I had no choice.

1232
01:28:42,364 --> 01:28:44,783
They arrived right before you did.

1233
01:28:44,867 --> 01:28:46,243
I’m sorry.

1234
01:28:50,414 --> 01:28:52,207
I’m sorry, too.

1235
01:28:54,376 --> 01:28:56,253
Gahhh.

1236
01:29:05,804 --> 01:29:07,472
<i>[Beep Beep Blip Blip]</i>

1237
01:29:07,556 --> 01:29:09,808
No, 3PO’s with them.

1238
01:29:09,892 --> 01:29:12,019
Just hang on. We’re almost there.

1239
01:29:15,564 --> 01:29:19,484
[Whistle Screeches]

1240
01:29:19,568 --> 01:29:22,070
Gahhh!

1241
01:29:22,154 --> 01:29:25,490
Gahhh!

1242
01:29:25,574 --> 01:29:27,534
[Whistle Stops]

1243
01:30:08,617 --> 01:30:10,494
Oh ah ooh ah.

1244
01:30:10,577 --> 01:30:13,080
Im trbly srry.

1245
01:30:13,163 --> 01:30:15,499
I dndt mn to intrddd.

1246
01:30:19,628 --> 01:30:22,089
No! Secret. Stormtroopers?

1247
01:30:22,172 --> 01:30:23,632
Here? We’re in danger!

1248
01:30:23,924 --> 01:30:25,884
I must tell the others.

1249
01:30:25,968 --> 01:30:28,053
Oh, no, I’ve been shot!

1250
01:30:46,655 --> 01:30:48,365
Aaah!

1251
01:30:48,448 --> 01:30:49,491
Aaah!

1252
01:30:49,575 --> 01:30:53,579
Aaaaahhh!

1253
01:30:55,163 --> 01:30:56,498
Lord Vader.

1254
01:30:56,582 --> 01:31:02,087
You may take Captain Solo to Jabba the Hutt
after I have Skywalker.

1255
01:31:02,171 --> 01:31:04,089
He’s no good to me dead.

1256
01:31:04,173 --> 01:31:07,092
He will not be permanently damaged.

1257
01:31:07,176 --> 01:31:09,261
Aaaahhh!

1258
01:31:09,344 --> 01:31:12,681
Lord Vader,
what about Leia and the Wookiee?

1259
01:31:12,931 --> 01:31:15,267
They must never again leave this city.

1260
01:31:15,350 --> 01:31:16,935
That was never a condition
of our agreement,

1261
01:31:17,019 --> 01:31:18,520
nor was giving Han to this bounty hunter.

1262
01:31:18,604 --> 01:31:23,692
Perhaps you think you’re being treated unfairly?

1263
01:31:23,984 --> 01:31:24,943
No.

1264
01:31:25,027 --> 01:31:30,115
Good. It would be unfortunate
if I had to leave a garrison here.

1265
01:31:30,199 --> 01:31:34,453
This deal is getting worse all the time.

1266
01:31:35,621 --> 01:31:38,540
Oh, yes, that’s very good.
I like that.

1267
01:31:38,624 --> 01:31:39,958
Oh!

1268
01:31:40,042 --> 01:31:42,544
Something’s not right
because now I can’t see.

1269
01:31:42,628 --> 01:31:46,715
Oh, oh, oh, that’s much better.

1270
01:31:46,965 --> 01:31:48,300
Wait! Wait!

1271
01:31:48,383 --> 01:31:50,302
Oh, my! What have you done?

1272
01:31:50,385 --> 01:31:52,304
I’m backwards,

1273
01:31:52,387 --> 01:31:54,306
you flea-bitten furball!

1274
01:31:54,389 --> 01:31:58,101
Only an overgrown mophead like you
would be stupid enough-

1275
01:32:11,532 --> 01:32:13,158
I feel terrible.

1276
01:32:13,242 --> 01:32:14,576
Gahhh.

1277
01:32:28,298 --> 01:32:30,592
Why are they doing this?

1278
01:32:33,720 --> 01:32:37,224
They never even asked me
any questions.

1279
01:32:40,561 --> 01:32:42,229
Lando.

1280
01:32:45,065 --> 01:32:46,066
Grrr!

1281
01:32:46,149 --> 01:32:47,234
Get out of here, Lando.

1282
01:32:47,317 --> 01:32:49,194
Shut up and listen!

1283
01:32:49,278 --> 01:32:51,488
Vader’s agreed
to turn Leia and Chewie over to me.

1284
01:32:51,572 --> 01:32:53,407
They’ll have to stay here,
but at least they’ll be safe.

1285
01:32:53,490 --> 01:32:54,491
Leia: What about Han?

1286
01:32:54,575 --> 01:32:55,701
Vader’s given him to the bounty hunter.

1287
01:32:55,784 --> 01:32:57,369
Vader wants us all dead.

1288
01:32:57,452 --> 01:32:59,705
He doesn’t want you at all.
He’s after somebody called Skywalker.

1289
01:32:59,788 --> 01:33:02,374
Luke.
Lord Vader set a trap for him.

1290
01:33:02,457 --> 01:33:04,459
And we’re the bait!

1291
01:33:04,543 --> 01:33:06,420
He’s on his way.

1292
01:33:06,503 --> 01:33:09,548
You fixed us all real good, didn’t you?

1293
01:33:09,631 --> 01:33:10,799
My friend.

1294
01:33:13,260 --> 01:33:14,344
Stop!

1295
01:33:16,388 --> 01:33:17,806
I’ve done all I can.

1296
01:33:18,056 --> 01:33:19,391
I’m sorry I couldn’t do better,

1297
01:33:19,474 --> 01:33:21,185
but I’ve got my own problems.

1298
01:33:21,268 --> 01:33:22,519
Yeah.

1299
01:33:22,603 --> 01:33:24,521
You’re a real hero.

1300
01:33:34,781 --> 01:33:37,451
You certainly have a way with people.

1301
01:33:41,246 --> 01:33:42,748
Ah...Ah...

1302
01:33:51,715 --> 01:33:54,092
This facility is crude,

1303
01:33:54,176 --> 01:33:59,473
but it should be adequate to freeze Skywalker
for his journey to the emperor.

1304
01:33:59,556 --> 01:34:02,434
Lord Vader,
ship approaching, X-wing class.

1305
01:34:02,518 --> 01:34:06,855
Good. Monitor Skywalker
and allow him to land.

1306
01:34:07,105 --> 01:34:10,400
Lord Vader,
we only use this facility for carbon freezing.

1307
01:34:10,484 --> 01:34:12,778
You put him in there, it might kill him.

1308
01:34:12,861 --> 01:34:15,781
I do not want
the emperor’s prize damaged.

1309
01:34:15,864 --> 01:34:18,450
We will test it on Captain Solo.

1310
01:34:40,889 --> 01:34:43,725
If only you’d attached my legs,

1311
01:34:43,809 --> 01:34:45,769
I wouldn’t be in
this ridiculous position.

1312
01:34:45,853 --> 01:34:47,354
Now remember, Chewbacca,

1313
01:34:47,437 --> 01:34:49,356
you have a responsibility for me,

1314
01:34:49,439 --> 01:34:51,358
so don’t do anything foolish.

1315
01:35:04,162 --> 01:35:05,747
What’s going on,

1316
01:35:05,831 --> 01:35:07,457
buddy?

1317
01:35:07,541 --> 01:35:10,502
You’re being put into carbon freeze.

1318
01:35:10,586 --> 01:35:13,922
What if he doesn’t survive?
He’s worth a lot to me.

1319
01:35:14,214 --> 01:35:16,675
The Empire will compensate you if he dies.

1320
01:35:16,758 --> 01:35:18,677
Put him in.

1321
01:35:18,760 --> 01:35:19,803
Rrrah!

1322
01:35:19,887 --> 01:35:22,389
Rrrah! Rrrah!

1323
01:35:22,472 --> 01:35:24,391
Han: Stop, Chewie, stop, stop!

1324
01:35:24,474 --> 01:35:27,936
3PO: Yes, stop, please! I’m not ready to die!

1325
01:35:28,187 --> 01:35:30,522
Hey! Hey! Listen to me, Chewie.

1326
01:35:30,606 --> 01:35:32,691
This won’t help me.

1327
01:35:32,774 --> 01:35:33,942
Hey, save your strength.

1328
01:35:34,234 --> 01:35:36,695
There will be another time.

1329
01:35:36,778 --> 01:35:38,864
The princess-

1330
01:35:38,947 --> 01:35:40,782
You have to take care of her.

1331
01:35:42,951 --> 01:35:45,329
Do you hear me? Huh?

1332
01:35:45,412 --> 01:35:46,663
Gahhh...

1333
01:35:58,842 --> 01:36:00,219
I love you.

1334
01:36:00,302 --> 01:36:01,845
I know.

1335
01:36:22,866 --> 01:36:24,451
Gahhh!

1336
01:36:30,999 --> 01:36:33,252
What’s going on? Turn around!

1337
01:36:33,335 --> 01:36:34,711
Chewbacca, I can’t see.

1338
01:36:48,851 --> 01:36:51,019
Gahhh.

1339
01:37:32,519 --> 01:37:35,814
Oh, they’ve encased him in carbonite.

1340
01:37:35,898 --> 01:37:37,649
He should be quite well-protected,

1341
01:37:37,733 --> 01:37:39,651
if he survived the freezing process, that is.

1342
01:37:39,735 --> 01:37:42,613
Well, Calrissian, did he survive?

1343
01:37:42,696 --> 01:37:44,573
Yes, he’s alive.

1344
01:37:44,656 --> 01:37:46,783
And in perfect hibernation.

1345
01:37:46,867 --> 01:37:49,828
He’s all yours, bounty hunter.

1346
01:37:49,912 --> 01:37:52,539
Reset the chamber for Skywalker.

1347
01:37:54,791 --> 01:37:56,710
Skywalker has just landed, lord.

1348
01:37:56,793 --> 01:38:00,756
Good. See to it that
he finds his way in here.

1349
01:38:04,927 --> 01:38:09,473
Calrissian, take the princess
and the Wookiee to my ship.

1350
01:38:09,556 --> 01:38:11,683
You said they’d be left in the city
under my supervision.

1351
01:38:11,767 --> 01:38:13,769
I am altering the deal.

1352
01:38:13,852 --> 01:38:16,688
Pray I don’t alter it any further.

1353
01:39:03,986 --> 01:39:05,696
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

1354
01:39:05,779 --> 01:39:07,656
<i>[Blip Blip]</i>

1355
01:39:16,081 --> 01:39:17,791
<i>[Blip Blip]</i>

1356
01:39:52,618 --> 01:39:53,785
Gahhh!

1357
01:39:53,869 --> 01:39:56,538
Luke! Luke, don’t, it’s a trap!

1358
01:39:57,915 --> 01:39:59,041
It’s a trap!

1359
01:40:21,772 --> 01:40:22,898
<i>[Beep]</i>

1360
01:40:44,211 --> 01:40:47,881
The Force is with you, young Skywalker.

1361
01:40:49,258 --> 01:40:52,261
But you are not a Jedi yet.

1362
01:41:53,655 --> 01:41:55,032
Well done.

1363
01:41:57,117 --> 01:41:59,620
Hold them in the security tower.

1364
01:41:59,703 --> 01:42:01,830
And keep it quiet. Move.

1365
01:42:06,835 --> 01:42:08,962
What do you think you’re doing?

1366
01:42:09,046 --> 01:42:10,088
We’re getting out of here.

1367
01:42:10,172 --> 01:42:11,965
I knew all along. It had to be a mistake.

1368
01:42:12,049 --> 01:42:14,927
Do you think that after what you did to Han,
we’re going to trust you?

1369
01:42:15,010 --> 01:42:15,844
Grrr!

1370
01:42:15,928 --> 01:42:17,638
I had no choice.

1371
01:42:17,721 --> 01:42:19,181
What are you doing? Trust him! Trust him!

1372
01:42:19,264 --> 01:42:22,267
We understand, don’t we, Chewie?
He had no choice.

1373
01:42:22,351 --> 01:42:24,019
I’m just trying to help.

1374
01:42:24,102 --> 01:42:26,355
We don’t need any of your help.

1375
01:42:26,605 --> 01:42:27,940
Haaa...

1376
01:42:28,023 --> 01:42:28,815
Grrr!

1377
01:42:28,899 --> 01:42:31,068
Ha...Ha...

1378
01:42:31,151 --> 01:42:32,152
What?

1379
01:42:32,236 --> 01:42:33,362
Han...

1380
01:42:33,612 --> 01:42:34,738
It sounds like Han.

1381
01:42:34,821 --> 01:42:38,116
There’s still a chance to save Han...

1382
01:42:38,200 --> 01:42:40,619
at the east...

1383
01:42:40,702 --> 01:42:42,287
platform.

1384
01:42:42,371 --> 01:42:43,372
Chewie.

1385
01:42:46,041 --> 01:42:48,752
I’m terribly sorry about all this.

1386
01:42:48,836 --> 01:42:50,629
After all, he’s only a Wookiee.

1387
01:42:50,712 --> 01:42:54,216
Put Captain Solo in the cargo hold.

1388
01:43:06,395 --> 01:43:09,231
<i>[Beep Blip Beep]</i>

1389
01:43:09,314 --> 01:43:11,817
R2, R2, where have you been?

1390
01:43:11,900 --> 01:43:13,735
Wait. Turn around, you woolly-

1391
01:43:13,819 --> 01:43:17,739
Hurry! Hurry!
We’re trying to save Han from the bounty hunter.

1392
01:43:19,116 --> 01:43:22,786
Well, at least you’re still in one piece.

1393
01:43:22,870 --> 01:43:25,247
Look what’s happened to me.

1394
01:43:37,176 --> 01:43:39,887
Oh, no! Chewie, they’re behind you!

1395
01:43:52,816 --> 01:43:55,110
You have learned much, young one.

1396
01:43:55,194 --> 01:43:57,279
You’ll find I’m full of surprises.

1397
01:44:08,290 --> 01:44:12,044
Your destiny lies with me, Skywalker.

1398
01:44:12,127 --> 01:44:15,214
Obi-Wan knew this to be true.

1399
01:44:15,297 --> 01:44:16,298
No.

1400
01:44:20,844 --> 01:44:21,803
Aaah!

1401
01:44:23,388 --> 01:44:24,932
All too easy.

1402
01:44:30,062 --> 01:44:34,483
Perhaps you’re not as strong
as the emperor thought.

1403
01:44:35,776 --> 01:44:37,319
Impressive.

1404
01:44:39,238 --> 01:44:40,822
Most impressive.

1405
01:44:43,492 --> 01:44:45,202
Aaah!

1406
01:44:48,163 --> 01:44:50,123
Obi-Wan has taught you well.

1407
01:44:50,207 --> 01:44:52,251
You have controlled your fear.

1408
01:44:54,127 --> 01:44:55,504
Now...

1409
01:44:55,796 --> 01:44:58,257
release your anger.

1410
01:44:58,340 --> 01:45:01,343
Only your hatred can destroy me.

1411
01:45:12,020 --> 01:45:13,230
Ohh!

1412
01:47:11,515 --> 01:47:13,934
The security code has been changed.

1413
01:47:14,017 --> 01:47:17,271
R2, you can tell the computer
to override the security systems.

1414
01:47:17,354 --> 01:47:19,648
R2, hurry!

1415
01:47:22,234 --> 01:47:24,278
Attention. This is Lando Calrissian.

1416
01:47:24,361 --> 01:47:26,905
Attention. The Empire
has taken control of the city.

1417
01:47:26,989 --> 01:47:30,534
I advise everyone to leave
before more imperial troops arrive.

1418
01:47:37,124 --> 01:47:38,292
This way.

1419
01:47:38,375 --> 01:47:40,919
Well, don’t blame me. I’m an interpreter.

1420
01:47:41,003 --> 01:47:45,132
I’m not supposed to know a power socket
from a computer terminal.

1421
01:48:03,233 --> 01:48:04,985
<i>[Beep Blip Beep Beep]</i>

1422
01:48:05,068 --> 01:48:08,530
<i>Ah! We’re not interested</i>
<i>in the Millennium Falcon’s hyperdrive.</i>

1423
01:48:08,614 --> 01:48:10,407
It’s fixed!

1424
01:48:12,284 --> 01:48:15,162
Just open the door, you stupid lump!

1425
01:48:23,712 --> 01:48:26,298
I never doubted you for a second.

1426
01:48:26,381 --> 01:48:27,424
Wonderful!

1427
01:48:50,239 --> 01:48:52,324
Ouch! Oh! That hurts!

1428
01:48:52,407 --> 01:48:54,576
Bend down, you thoughtless-Ow!

1429
01:48:59,206 --> 01:49:01,083
Leia!

1430
01:49:01,667 --> 01:49:03,210
Go!

1431
01:49:08,006 --> 01:49:11,677
I thought that hairy beast
would be the end of me.

1432
01:49:11,760 --> 01:49:12,761
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

1433
01:49:13,011 --> 01:49:14,388
Of course I’ve looked better.

1434
01:50:08,108 --> 01:50:09,484
You are beaten.

1435
01:50:09,568 --> 01:50:11,653
It is useless to resist.

1436
01:50:11,737 --> 01:50:15,365
Don’t let yourself be destroyed
as Obi-Wan did.

1437
01:50:21,121 --> 01:50:22,831
Uh!

1438
01:50:26,126 --> 01:50:28,337
Aah!

1439
01:50:29,838 --> 01:50:32,716
There is no escape.

1440
01:50:32,799 --> 01:50:35,719
Don’t make me destroy you.

1441
01:50:37,721 --> 01:50:38,764
Luke,

1442
01:50:38,847 --> 01:50:42,309
you do not yet realize your importance.

1443
01:50:42,392 --> 01:50:45,354
You have only begun to discover your power.

1444
01:50:45,437 --> 01:50:49,733
Join me, and I will complete your training.

1445
01:50:49,816 --> 01:50:52,194
With our combined strength,

1446
01:50:52,277 --> 01:50:57,741
we can end this destructive conflict
and bring order to the galaxy.

1447
01:50:57,824 --> 01:50:59,368
I’ll never join you!

1448
01:50:59,451 --> 01:51:04,331
If you only knew the power
of the dark side.

1449
01:51:04,414 --> 01:51:08,627
Obi-Wan never told you
what happened to your father.

1450
01:51:08,710 --> 01:51:10,504
He told me enough.

1451
01:51:13,173 --> 01:51:14,883
He told me you killed him.

1452
01:51:15,133 --> 01:51:16,510
No.

1453
01:51:16,593 --> 01:51:18,762
<i>I am your father.</i>

1454
01:51:22,850 --> 01:51:24,893
No.

1455
01:51:25,185 --> 01:51:26,562
No.

1456
01:51:26,645 --> 01:51:29,815
That’s not true.

1457
01:51:29,898 --> 01:51:31,733
That’s impossible!

1458
01:51:31,817 --> 01:51:35,237
Search your feelings. You know it to be true.

1459
01:51:36,405 --> 01:51:38,907
No!

1460
01:51:39,199 --> 01:51:42,411
No!

1461
01:51:42,494 --> 01:51:43,829
Luke.

1462
01:51:43,912 --> 01:51:46,164
You can destroy the emperor.

1463
01:51:46,248 --> 01:51:48,208
He has foreseen this.

1464
01:51:48,292 --> 01:51:50,919
It is your destiny.

1465
01:51:51,211 --> 01:51:57,467
Join me, and together
we can rule the galaxy as father and son.

1466
01:52:07,936 --> 01:52:09,646
Come with me.

1467
01:52:09,730 --> 01:52:12,691
It is the only way.

1468
01:53:18,590 --> 01:53:20,759
Ben.

1469
01:53:20,843 --> 01:53:23,011
Ben, please.

1470
01:53:31,937 --> 01:53:33,522
Ben.

1471
01:53:38,694 --> 01:53:39,987
Leia.

1472
01:53:50,289 --> 01:53:52,040
Hear me.

1473
01:53:53,750 --> 01:53:55,043
Leia.

1474
01:53:55,294 --> 01:53:56,712
Luke.

1475
01:53:58,797 --> 01:54:00,716
We’ve got to go back.

1476
01:54:00,799 --> 01:54:02,759
What?
I know where Luke is.

1477
01:54:02,843 --> 01:54:03,969
What about those fighters?

1478
01:54:04,052 --> 01:54:06,305
Chewie, just do it.

1479
01:54:06,388 --> 01:54:07,723
But what about Vader?

1480
01:54:07,806 --> 01:54:09,391
All right, all right!

1481
01:54:16,857 --> 01:54:21,612
Alert my Stardestroyer
to prepare for my arrival.

1482
01:54:30,829 --> 01:54:33,749
Look, someone’s up there.

1483
01:54:35,083 --> 01:54:36,376
It’s Luke.

1484
01:54:36,460 --> 01:54:37,836
Chewie, slow down.

1485
01:54:37,920 --> 01:54:39,838
Slow down. We’ll get under him.

1486
01:54:39,922 --> 01:54:42,424
Lando, open the top hatch.

1487
01:54:57,105 --> 01:54:58,357
O.K.

1488
01:54:58,440 --> 01:54:59,566
Easy, Chewie.

1489
01:54:59,650 --> 01:55:00,692
Gahrrr.

1490
01:55:21,380 --> 01:55:22,381
Lando?

1491
01:55:22,464 --> 01:55:23,549
<i>O.K., let’s go.</i>

1492
01:55:40,649 --> 01:55:42,818
Oh, Leia.

1493
01:55:42,901 --> 01:55:44,903
All right, Chewie, let’s go.

1494
01:56:20,022 --> 01:56:21,523
I’ll be back.

1495
01:56:27,988 --> 01:56:29,531
Stardestroyer.

1496
01:56:34,703 --> 01:56:36,955
All right, Chewie. Ready for light speed.

1497
01:56:37,039 --> 01:56:39,458
<i>If your people fixed the hyperdrive.</i>

1498
01:56:39,541 --> 01:56:41,793
All the coordinates are set.
It’s now or never.

1499
01:56:41,877 --> 01:56:43,962
Punch it!

1500
01:56:44,046 --> 01:56:46,548
[Engine Coughs]

1501
01:56:54,014 --> 01:56:56,475
They told me they fixed it.

1502
01:56:56,558 --> 01:56:58,477
I trusted them!

1503
01:56:58,560 --> 01:57:00,979
It’s not my fault!

1504
01:57:05,943 --> 01:57:08,987
They’ll be in range of
our tractor beam in moments, lord.

1505
01:57:09,071 --> 01:57:12,866
<i>Did your men deactivate</i>
<i>the hyperdrive on the Millennium Falcon?</i>

1506
01:57:12,950 --> 01:57:13,951
Yes, my lord.

1507
01:57:14,034 --> 01:57:18,830
Good. Prepare the boarding party
and set your weapons for "stun."

1508
01:57:18,914 --> 01:57:20,749
Yes, my lord. Lieutenant.

1509
01:57:20,832 --> 01:57:21,959
Yes, sir.

1510
01:57:23,585 --> 01:57:26,255
Noisy brute.
Why don’t we just go into light speed?

1511
01:57:26,547 --> 01:57:27,840
<i>[Beep Beep Blip Beep]</i>

1512
01:57:27,923 --> 01:57:31,009
We can’t? How would you know
the hyperdrive is deactivated?

1513
01:57:31,093 --> 01:57:34,137
<i>[Blip Beep Beep Blip]</i>

1514
01:57:34,221 --> 01:57:36,682
The city’s central computer told you?

1515
01:57:36,765 --> 01:57:40,018
R2-D2, you know better
than to trust a strange computer.

1516
01:57:40,102 --> 01:57:41,144
Ouch!

1517
01:57:41,228 --> 01:57:43,605
Pay attention to what you’re doing!

1518
01:57:53,907 --> 01:57:55,617
Luke.

1519
01:57:55,701 --> 01:57:57,870
Father.

1520
01:57:57,953 --> 01:58:01,832
Son, come with me.

1521
01:58:03,709 --> 01:58:05,127
Ben.

1522
01:58:06,545 --> 01:58:08,547
Why didn’t you tell me?

1523
01:58:13,760 --> 01:58:15,721
Chewie!

1524
01:58:26,773 --> 01:58:28,025
It’s Vader.

1525
01:58:33,864 --> 01:58:37,242
Luke, it is your destiny.

1526
01:58:42,080 --> 01:58:44,333
Ben.

1527
01:58:44,583 --> 01:58:46,960
Why didn’t you tell me?

1528
01:58:53,759 --> 01:58:55,594
Alert all commands.

1529
01:58:55,677 --> 01:58:57,763
Ready for the tractor beam.

1530
01:58:59,973 --> 01:59:01,892
R2, come back at once!

1531
01:59:01,975 --> 01:59:03,894
You haven’t finished with me yet.

1532
01:59:03,977 --> 01:59:05,771
You don’t know how to fix the hyperdrive.

1533
01:59:05,854 --> 01:59:07,147
Chewbacca can do it.

1534
01:59:07,231 --> 01:59:08,774
I’m standing here in pieces,

1535
01:59:08,857 --> 01:59:12,069
and you’re having delusions of grandeur!

1536
01:59:14,613 --> 01:59:16,782
You did it!

1537
02:00:13,422 --> 02:00:16,049
Luke, we’re ready for takeoff.

1538
02:00:16,133 --> 02:00:17,342
<i>Good luck, Lando.</i>

1539
02:00:17,426 --> 02:00:21,054
<i>When we find Jabba the Hutt</i>
<i>and that bounty hunter,</i>

1540
02:00:21,138 --> 02:00:22,347
<i>we’ll contact you.</i>

1541
02:00:22,431 --> 02:00:25,142
I’ll meet you
at the rendezvous point on Tatooine.

1542
02:00:25,225 --> 02:00:27,269
Princess, we’ll find Han.

1543
02:00:27,352 --> 02:00:28,770
I promise.

1544
02:00:28,854 --> 02:00:31,023
Chewie, I’ll be waiting for your signal.

1545
02:00:31,106 --> 02:00:32,900
Take care, you two.

1546
02:00:32,983 --> 02:00:34,860
<i>May the Force be with you.</i>

1547
02:00:34,943 --> 02:00:36,361
Gahhh.

1548
02:00:36,445 --> 02:00:39,072
<i>Gahhh.</i>

1549
02:00:48,123 --> 02:00:49,124
Ow.

1550
02:01:11,271 --> 02:01:14,191
<i>[Beep Blip Blip Beep]</i>

1551
02:01:32,835 --> 02:01:34,837
<i>[Beep Blip]</i>

